110// Pragma STDC implementations.
111
112/// PragmaSTDC_FENV_ACCESSHandler - "\#pragma STDC FENV_ACCESS ...".
113struct PragmaSTDC_FENV_ACCESSHandler : public PragmaHandler {
114 PragmaSTDC_FENV_ACCESSHandler() : PragmaHandler("FENV_ACCESS") {}
115
116 void HandlePragma(Preprocessor &PP, PragmaIntroducer Introducer,
117 Token &Tok) override {
118 tok::OnOffSwitch OOS;
119 if (PP.LexOnOffSwitch(OOS))
120 return;
121 if (OOS == tok::OOS_ON) {
122 PP.Diag(Tok, diag::warn_stdc_fenv_access_not_supported);
123 }
124
125 MutableArrayRef<Token> Toks(PP.getPreprocessorAllocator().Allocate<Token>(1),
126 1);
127 Toks[0].startToken();
128 Toks[0].setKind(tok::annot_pragma_fenv_access);
129 Toks[0].setLocation(Tok.getLocation());
130 Toks[0].setAnnotationEndLoc(Tok.getLocation());
131 Toks[0].setAnnotationValue(reinterpret_cast<void*>(
132 static_cast<uintptr_t>(OOS)));
133 PP.EnterTokenStream(Toks, /*DisableMacroExpansion=*/true,
134 /*IsReinject=*/false);
135 }
136};
137
138/// PragmaSTDC_CX_LIMITED_RANGEHandler - "\#pragma STDC CX_LIMITED_RANGE ...".
139struct PragmaSTDC_CX_LIMITED_RANGEHandler : public PragmaHandler {
140 PragmaSTDC_CX_LIMITED_RANGEHandler() : PragmaHandler("CX_LIMITED_RANGE") {}
141
142 void HandlePragma(Preprocessor &PP, PragmaIntroducer Introducer,
143 Token &Tok) override {
144 tok::OnOffSwitch OOS;
145 PP.LexOnOffSwitch(OOS);
146 }

290void Parser::initializePragmaHandlers() {
291 AlignHandler = llvm::make_unique<PragmaAlignHandler>();
292 PP.AddPragmaHandler(AlignHandler.get());
293
294 GCCVisibilityHandler = llvm::make_unique<PragmaGCCVisibilityHandler>();
295 PP.AddPragmaHandler("GCC", GCCVisibilityHandler.get());
296
297 OptionsHandler = llvm::make_unique<PragmaOptionsHandler>();
298 PP.AddPragmaHandler(OptionsHandler.get());
299
300 PackHandler = llvm::make_unique<PragmaPackHandler>();
301 PP.AddPragmaHandler(PackHandler.get());
302
303 MSStructHandler = llvm::make_unique<PragmaMSStructHandler>();
304 PP.AddPragmaHandler(MSStructHandler.get());
305
306 UnusedHandler = llvm::make_unique<PragmaUnusedHandler>();
307 PP.AddPragmaHandler(UnusedHandler.get());
308
309 WeakHandler = llvm::make_unique<PragmaWeakHandler>();
310 PP.AddPragmaHandler(WeakHandler.get());
311
312 RedefineExtnameHandler = llvm::make_unique<PragmaRedefineExtnameHandler>();
313 PP.AddPragmaHandler(RedefineExtnameHandler.get());
314
315 OpaqueHandler = llvm::make_unique<PragmaOpaqueHandler>(Actions);
316 PP.AddPragmaHandler(OpaqueHandler.get());
317
318 FPContractHandler = llvm::make_unique<PragmaFPContractHandler>();
319 PP.AddPragmaHandler("STDC", FPContractHandler.get());
320
321 STDCFENVHandler = llvm::make_unique<PragmaSTDC_FENV_ACCESSHandler>();
322 PP.AddPragmaHandler("STDC", STDCFENVHandler.get());
323
324 STDCCXLIMITHandler = llvm::make_unique<PragmaSTDC_CX_LIMITED_RANGEHandler>();
325 PP.AddPragmaHandler("STDC", STDCCXLIMITHandler.get());
326
327 STDCUnknownHandler = llvm::make_unique<PragmaSTDC_UnknownHandler>();
328 PP.AddPragmaHandler("STDC", STDCUnknownHandler.get());
329
330 PCSectionHandler = llvm::make_unique<PragmaClangSectionHandler>(Actions);
331 PP.AddPragmaHandler("clang", PCSectionHandler.get());
332
333 if (getLangOpts().OpenCL) {
334 OpenCLExtensionHandler = llvm::make_unique<PragmaOpenCLExtensionHandler>();
335 PP.AddPragmaHandler("OPENCL", OpenCLExtensionHandler.get());
336
337 PP.AddPragmaHandler("OPENCL", FPContractHandler.get());
338 }
339 if (getLangOpts().OpenMP)
340 OpenMPHandler = llvm::make_unique<PragmaOpenMPHandler>();
341 else
342 OpenMPHandler = llvm::make_unique<PragmaNoOpenMPHandler>();
343 PP.AddPragmaHandler(OpenMPHandler.get());
344
345 PointerInterpretationHandler = llvm::make_unique<PragmaPointerInterpretation>(Actions);
346 PP.AddPragmaHandler(PointerInterpretationHandler.get());
347
348 if (getLangOpts().MicrosoftExt ||
349 getTargetInfo().getTriple().isOSBinFormatELF()) {
350 MSCommentHandler = llvm::make_unique<PragmaCommentHandler>(Actions);
351 PP.AddPragmaHandler(MSCommentHandler.get());
352 }
353
354 if (getLangOpts().MicrosoftExt) {
355 MSDetectMismatchHandler =
356 llvm::make_unique<PragmaDetectMismatchHandler>(Actions);
357 PP.AddPragmaHandler(MSDetectMismatchHandler.get());
358 MSPointersToMembers = llvm::make_unique<PragmaMSPointersToMembers>();
359 PP.AddPragmaHandler(MSPointersToMembers.get());
360 MSVtorDisp = llvm::make_unique<PragmaMSVtorDisp>();
361 PP.AddPragmaHandler(MSVtorDisp.get());
362 MSInitSeg = llvm::make_unique<PragmaMSPragma>("init_seg");
363 PP.AddPragmaHandler(MSInitSeg.get());
364 MSDataSeg = llvm::make_unique<PragmaMSPragma>("data_seg");
365 PP.AddPragmaHandler(MSDataSeg.get());
366 MSBSSSeg = llvm::make_unique<PragmaMSPragma>("bss_seg");
367 PP.AddPragmaHandler(MSBSSSeg.get());
368 MSConstSeg = llvm::make_unique<PragmaMSPragma>("const_seg");
369 PP.AddPragmaHandler(MSConstSeg.get());
370 MSCodeSeg = llvm::make_unique<PragmaMSPragma>("code_seg");
371 PP.AddPragmaHandler(MSCodeSeg.get());
372 MSSection = llvm::make_unique<PragmaMSPragma>("section");
373 PP.AddPragmaHandler(MSSection.get());
374 MSRuntimeChecks = llvm::make_unique<PragmaMSRuntimeChecksHandler>();
375 PP.AddPragmaHandler(MSRuntimeChecks.get());
376 MSIntrinsic = llvm::make_unique<PragmaMSIntrinsicHandler>();
377 PP.AddPragmaHandler(MSIntrinsic.get());
378 MSOptimize = llvm::make_unique<PragmaMSOptimizeHandler>();
379 PP.AddPragmaHandler(MSOptimize.get());
380 }
381
382 if (getLangOpts().CUDA) {
383 CUDAForceHostDeviceHandler =
384 llvm::make_unique<PragmaForceCUDAHostDeviceHandler>(Actions);
385 PP.AddPragmaHandler("clang", CUDAForceHostDeviceHandler.get());
386 }
387
388 OptimizeHandler = llvm::make_unique<PragmaOptimizeHandler>(Actions);
389 PP.AddPragmaHandler("clang", OptimizeHandler.get());
390
391 LoopHintHandler = llvm::make_unique<PragmaLoopHintHandler>();
392 PP.AddPragmaHandler("clang", LoopHintHandler.get());
393
394 UnrollHintHandler = llvm::make_unique<PragmaUnrollHintHandler>("unroll");
395 PP.AddPragmaHandler(UnrollHintHandler.get());
396
397 NoUnrollHintHandler = llvm::make_unique<PragmaUnrollHintHandler>("nounroll");
398 PP.AddPragmaHandler(NoUnrollHintHandler.get());
399
400 UnrollAndJamHintHandler =
401 llvm::make_unique<PragmaUnrollHintHandler>("unroll_and_jam");
402 PP.AddPragmaHandler(UnrollAndJamHintHandler.get());
403
404 NoUnrollAndJamHintHandler =
405 llvm::make_unique<PragmaUnrollHintHandler>("nounroll_and_jam");
406 PP.AddPragmaHandler(NoUnrollAndJamHintHandler.get());
407
408 FPHandler = llvm::make_unique<PragmaFPHandler>();
409 PP.AddPragmaHandler("clang", FPHandler.get());
410
411 AttributePragmaHandler =
412 llvm::make_unique<PragmaAttributeHandler>(AttrFactory);
413 PP.AddPragmaHandler("clang", AttributePragmaHandler.get());
414}

416void Parser::resetPragmaHandlers() {
417 // Remove the pragma handlers we installed.
418 PP.RemovePragmaHandler(AlignHandler.get());
419 AlignHandler.reset();
420 PP.RemovePragmaHandler("GCC", GCCVisibilityHandler.get());
421 GCCVisibilityHandler.reset();
422 PP.RemovePragmaHandler(OptionsHandler.get());
423 OptionsHandler.reset();
424 PP.RemovePragmaHandler(PointerInterpretationHandler.get());
425 PointerInterpretationHandler.reset();
426 PP.RemovePragmaHandler(PackHandler.get());
427 PackHandler.reset();
428 PP.RemovePragmaHandler(MSStructHandler.get());
429 MSStructHandler.reset();
430 PP.RemovePragmaHandler(UnusedHandler.get());
431 UnusedHandler.reset();
432 PP.RemovePragmaHandler(WeakHandler.get());
433 WeakHandler.reset();
434 PP.RemovePragmaHandler(RedefineExtnameHandler.get());
435 RedefineExtnameHandler.reset();
436 PP.RemovePragmaHandler(OpaqueHandler.get());
437 OpaqueHandler.reset();
438
439 if (getLangOpts().OpenCL) {
440 PP.RemovePragmaHandler("OPENCL", OpenCLExtensionHandler.get());
441 OpenCLExtensionHandler.reset();
442 PP.RemovePragmaHandler("OPENCL", FPContractHandler.get());
443 }
444 PP.RemovePragmaHandler(OpenMPHandler.get());
445 OpenMPHandler.reset();
446
447 if (getLangOpts().MicrosoftExt ||
448 getTargetInfo().getTriple().isOSBinFormatELF()) {
449 PP.RemovePragmaHandler(MSCommentHandler.get());
450 MSCommentHandler.reset();
451 }
452
453 PP.RemovePragmaHandler("clang", PCSectionHandler.get());
454 PCSectionHandler.reset();
455
456 if (getLangOpts().MicrosoftExt) {
457 PP.RemovePragmaHandler(MSDetectMismatchHandler.get());
458 MSDetectMismatchHandler.reset();
459 PP.RemovePragmaHandler(MSPointersToMembers.get());
460 MSPointersToMembers.reset();
461 PP.RemovePragmaHandler(MSVtorDisp.get());
462 MSVtorDisp.reset();
463 PP.RemovePragmaHandler(MSInitSeg.get());
464 MSInitSeg.reset();
465 PP.RemovePragmaHandler(MSDataSeg.get());
466 MSDataSeg.reset();
467 PP.RemovePragmaHandler(MSBSSSeg.get());
468 MSBSSSeg.reset();
469 PP.RemovePragmaHandler(MSConstSeg.get());
470 MSConstSeg.reset();
471 PP.RemovePragmaHandler(MSCodeSeg.get());
472 MSCodeSeg.reset();
473 PP.RemovePragmaHandler(MSSection.get());
474 MSSection.reset();
475 PP.RemovePragmaHandler(MSRuntimeChecks.get());
476 MSRuntimeChecks.reset();
477 PP.RemovePragmaHandler(MSIntrinsic.get());
478 MSIntrinsic.reset();
479 PP.RemovePragmaHandler(MSOptimize.get());
480 MSOptimize.reset();
481 }
482
483 if (getLangOpts().CUDA) {
484 PP.RemovePragmaHandler("clang", CUDAForceHostDeviceHandler.get());
485 CUDAForceHostDeviceHandler.reset();
486 }
487
488 PP.RemovePragmaHandler("STDC", FPContractHandler.get());
489 FPContractHandler.reset();
490
491 PP.RemovePragmaHandler("STDC", STDCFENVHandler.get());
492 STDCFENVHandler.reset();
493
494 PP.RemovePragmaHandler("STDC", STDCCXLIMITHandler.get());
495 STDCCXLIMITHandler.reset();
496
497 PP.RemovePragmaHandler("STDC", STDCUnknownHandler.get());
498 STDCUnknownHandler.reset();
499
500 PP.RemovePragmaHandler("clang", OptimizeHandler.get());
501 OptimizeHandler.reset();
502
503 PP.RemovePragmaHandler("clang", LoopHintHandler.get());
504 LoopHintHandler.reset();
505
506 PP.RemovePragmaHandler(UnrollHintHandler.get());
507 UnrollHintHandler.reset();
508
509 PP.RemovePragmaHandler(NoUnrollHintHandler.get());
510 NoUnrollHintHandler.reset();
511
512 PP.RemovePragmaHandler(UnrollAndJamHintHandler.get());
513 UnrollAndJamHintHandler.reset();
514
515 PP.RemovePragmaHandler(NoUnrollAndJamHintHandler.get());
516 NoUnrollAndJamHintHandler.reset();
517
518 PP.RemovePragmaHandler("clang", FPHandler.get());
519 FPHandler.reset();
520
521 PP.RemovePragmaHandler("clang", AttributePragmaHandler.get());
522 AttributePragmaHandler.reset();
523}

525/// Handle the annotation token produced for #pragma unused(...)
526///
527/// Each annot_pragma_unused is followed by the argument token so e.g.
528/// "#pragma unused(x,y)" becomes:
529/// annot_pragma_unused 'x' annot_pragma_unused 'y'
530void Parser::HandlePragmaUnused() {
531 assert(Tok.is(tok::annot_pragma_unused));
532 SourceLocation UnusedLoc = ConsumeAnnotationToken();
533 Actions.ActOnPragmaUnused(Tok, getCurScope(), UnusedLoc);
534 ConsumeToken(); // The argument token.
535}
536
537void Parser::HandlePragmaVisibility() {
538 assert(Tok.is(tok::annot_pragma_vis));
539 const IdentifierInfo *VisType =
540 static_cast<IdentifierInfo *>(Tok.getAnnotationValue());
541 SourceLocation VisLoc = ConsumeAnnotationToken();
542 Actions.ActOnPragmaVisibility(VisType, VisLoc);
543}

545namespace {
546struct PragmaPackInfo {
547 Sema::PragmaMsStackAction Action;
548 StringRef SlotLabel;
549 Token Alignment;
550};
551} // end anonymous namespace
552
553void Parser::HandlePragmaPack() {
554 assert(Tok.is(tok::annot_pragma_pack));
555 PragmaPackInfo *Info =
556 static_cast<PragmaPackInfo *>(Tok.getAnnotationValue());
557 SourceLocation PragmaLoc = Tok.getLocation();
558 ExprResult Alignment;
559 if (Info->Alignment.is(tok::numeric_constant)) {
560 Alignment = Actions.ActOnNumericConstant(Info->Alignment);
561 if (Alignment.isInvalid()) {
562 ConsumeAnnotationToken();
563 return;
564 }
565 }
566 Actions.ActOnPragmaPack(PragmaLoc, Info->Action, Info->SlotLabel,
567 Alignment.get());
568 // Consume the token after processing the pragma to enable pragma-specific
569 // #include warnings.
570 ConsumeAnnotationToken();
571}
572
573void Parser::HandlePragmaMSStruct() {
574 assert(Tok.is(tok::annot_pragma_msstruct));
575 PragmaMSStructKind Kind = static_cast<PragmaMSStructKind>(
576 reinterpret_cast<uintptr_t>(Tok.getAnnotationValue()));
577 Actions.ActOnPragmaMSStruct(Kind);
578 ConsumeAnnotationToken();
579}
580
581void Parser::HandlePragmaAlign() {
582 assert(Tok.is(tok::annot_pragma_align));
583 Sema::PragmaOptionsAlignKind Kind =
584 static_cast<Sema::PragmaOptionsAlignKind>(
585 reinterpret_cast<uintptr_t>(Tok.getAnnotationValue()));
586 Actions.ActOnPragmaOptionsAlign(Kind, Tok.getLocation());
587 // Consume the token after processing the pragma to enable pragma-specific
588 // #include warnings.
589 ConsumeAnnotationToken();
590}
591
592void Parser::HandlePragmaDump() {
593 assert(Tok.is(tok::annot_pragma_dump));
594 IdentifierInfo *II =
595 reinterpret_cast<IdentifierInfo *>(Tok.getAnnotationValue());
596 Actions.ActOnPragmaDump(getCurScope(), Tok.getLocation(), II);
597 ConsumeAnnotationToken();
598}
599
600void Parser::HandlePragmaWeak() {
601 assert(Tok.is(tok::annot_pragma_weak));
602 SourceLocation PragmaLoc = ConsumeAnnotationToken();
603 Actions.ActOnPragmaWeakID(Tok.getIdentifierInfo(), PragmaLoc,
604 Tok.getLocation());
605 ConsumeToken(); // The weak name.
606}
607
608void Parser::HandlePragmaWeakAlias() {
609 assert(Tok.is(tok::annot_pragma_weakalias));
610 SourceLocation PragmaLoc = ConsumeAnnotationToken();
611 IdentifierInfo *WeakName = Tok.getIdentifierInfo();
612 SourceLocation WeakNameLoc = Tok.getLocation();
613 ConsumeToken();
614 IdentifierInfo *AliasName = Tok.getIdentifierInfo();
615 SourceLocation AliasNameLoc = Tok.getLocation();
616 ConsumeToken();
617 Actions.ActOnPragmaWeakAlias(WeakName, AliasName, PragmaLoc,
618 WeakNameLoc, AliasNameLoc);
619
620}
621
622void Parser::HandlePragmaRedefineExtname() {
623 assert(Tok.is(tok::annot_pragma_redefine_extname));
624 SourceLocation RedefLoc = ConsumeAnnotationToken();
625 IdentifierInfo *RedefName = Tok.getIdentifierInfo();
626 SourceLocation RedefNameLoc = Tok.getLocation();
627 ConsumeToken();
628 IdentifierInfo *AliasName = Tok.getIdentifierInfo();
629 SourceLocation AliasNameLoc = Tok.getLocation();
630 ConsumeToken();
631 Actions.ActOnPragmaRedefineExtname(RedefName, AliasName, RedefLoc,
632 RedefNameLoc, AliasNameLoc);
633}
634
635void Parser::HandlePragmaFPContract() {
636 assert(Tok.is(tok::annot_pragma_fp_contract));
637 tok::OnOffSwitch OOS =
638 static_cast<tok::OnOffSwitch>(
639 reinterpret_cast<uintptr_t>(Tok.getAnnotationValue()));
640
641 LangOptions::FPContractModeKind FPC;
642 switch (OOS) {
643 case tok::OOS_ON:
644 FPC = LangOptions::FPC_On;
645 break;
646 case tok::OOS_OFF:
647 FPC = LangOptions::FPC_Off;
648 break;
649 case tok::OOS_DEFAULT:
650 FPC = getLangOpts().getDefaultFPContractMode();
651 break;
652 }
653
654 Actions.ActOnPragmaFPContract(FPC);
655 ConsumeAnnotationToken();
656}
657
658void Parser::HandlePragmaFEnvAccess() {
659 assert(Tok.is(tok::annot_pragma_fenv_access));
660 tok::OnOffSwitch OOS =
661 static_cast<tok::OnOffSwitch>(
662 reinterpret_cast<uintptr_t>(Tok.getAnnotationValue()));
663
664 LangOptions::FEnvAccessModeKind FPC;
665 switch (OOS) {
666 case tok::OOS_ON:
667 FPC = LangOptions::FEA_On;
668 break;
669 case tok::OOS_OFF:
670 FPC = LangOptions::FEA_Off;
671 break;
672 case tok::OOS_DEFAULT: // FIXME: Add this cli option when it makes sense.
673 FPC = LangOptions::FEA_Off;
674 break;
675 }
676
677 Actions.ActOnPragmaFEnvAccess(FPC);
678 ConsumeAnnotationToken();
679}
680
681
682StmtResult Parser::HandlePragmaCaptured()
683{
684 assert(Tok.is(tok::annot_pragma_captured));
685 ConsumeAnnotationToken();
686
687 if (Tok.isNot(tok::l_brace)) {
688 PP.Diag(Tok, diag::err_expected) << tok::l_brace;
689 return StmtError();
690 }
691
692 SourceLocation Loc = Tok.getLocation();
693
694 ParseScope CapturedRegionScope(this, Scope::FnScope | Scope::DeclScope |
695 Scope::CompoundStmtScope);
696 Actions.ActOnCapturedRegionStart(Loc, getCurScope(), CR_Default,
697 /*NumParams=*/1);
698
699 StmtResult R = ParseCompoundStatement();
700 CapturedRegionScope.Exit();
701
702 if (R.isInvalid()) {
703 Actions.ActOnCapturedRegionError();
704 return StmtError();
705 }
706
707 return Actions.ActOnCapturedRegionEnd(R.get());
708}

710namespace {
711 enum OpenCLExtState : char {
712 Disable, Enable, Begin, End
713 };
714 typedef std::pair<const IdentifierInfo *, OpenCLExtState> OpenCLExtData;
715}
716
717void Parser::HandlePragmaOpenCLExtension() {
718 assert(Tok.is(tok::annot_pragma_opencl_extension));
719 OpenCLExtData *Data = static_cast<OpenCLExtData*>(Tok.getAnnotationValue());
720 auto State = Data->second;
721 auto Ident = Data->first;
722 SourceLocation NameLoc = Tok.getLocation();
723 ConsumeAnnotationToken();
724
725 auto &Opt = Actions.getOpenCLOptions();
726 auto Name = Ident->getName();
727 // OpenCL 1.1 9.1: "The all variant sets the behavior for all extensions,
728 // overriding all previously issued extension directives, but only if the
729 // behavior is set to disable."
730 if (Name == "all") {
731 if (State == Disable) {
732 Opt.disableAll();
733 Opt.enableSupportedCore(getLangOpts());
734 } else {
735 PP.Diag(NameLoc, diag::warn_pragma_expected_predicate) << 1;
736 }
737 } else if (State == Begin) {
738 if (!Opt.isKnown(Name) || !Opt.isSupported(Name, getLangOpts())) {
739 Opt.support(Name);
740 }
741 Actions.setCurrentOpenCLExtension(Name);
742 } else if (State == End) {
743 if (Name != Actions.getCurrentOpenCLExtension())
744 PP.Diag(NameLoc, diag::warn_pragma_begin_end_mismatch);
745 Actions.setCurrentOpenCLExtension("");
746 } else if (!Opt.isKnown(Name))
747 PP.Diag(NameLoc, diag::warn_pragma_unknown_extension) << Ident;
748 else if (Opt.isSupportedExtension(Name, getLangOpts()))
749 Opt.enable(Name, State == Enable);
750 else if (Opt.isSupportedCore(Name, getLangOpts()))
751 PP.Diag(NameLoc, diag::warn_pragma_extension_is_core) << Ident;
752 else
753 PP.Diag(NameLoc, diag::warn_pragma_unsupported_extension) << Ident;
754}

756void Parser::HandlePragmaMSPointersToMembers() {
757 assert(Tok.is(tok::annot_pragma_ms_pointers_to_members));
758 LangOptions::PragmaMSPointersToMembersKind RepresentationMethod =
759 static_cast<LangOptions::PragmaMSPointersToMembersKind>(
760 reinterpret_cast<uintptr_t>(Tok.getAnnotationValue()));
761 SourceLocation PragmaLoc = ConsumeAnnotationToken();
762 Actions.ActOnPragmaMSPointersToMembers(RepresentationMethod, PragmaLoc);
763}

765void Parser::HandlePragmaMSVtorDisp() {
766 assert(Tok.is(tok::annot_pragma_ms_vtordisp));
767 uintptr_t Value = reinterpret_cast<uintptr_t>(Tok.getAnnotationValue());
768 Sema::PragmaMsStackAction Action =
769 static_cast<Sema::PragmaMsStackAction>((Value >> 16) & 0xFFFF);
770 MSVtorDispAttr::Mode Mode = MSVtorDispAttr::Mode(Value & 0xFFFF);
771 SourceLocation PragmaLoc = ConsumeAnnotationToken();
772 Actions.ActOnPragmaMSVtorDisp(Action, PragmaLoc, Mode);
773}
774
775void Parser::HandlePragmaMSPragma() {
776 assert(Tok.is(tok::annot_pragma_ms_pragma));
777 // Grab the tokens out of the annotation and enter them into the stream.
778 auto TheTokens =
779 (std::pair<std::unique_ptr<Token[]>, size_t> *)Tok.getAnnotationValue();
780 PP.EnterTokenStream(std::move(TheTokens->first), TheTokens->second, true,
781 /*IsReinject=*/true);
782 SourceLocation PragmaLocation = ConsumeAnnotationToken();
783 assert(Tok.isAnyIdentifier());
784 StringRef PragmaName = Tok.getIdentifierInfo()->getName();
785 PP.Lex(Tok); // pragma kind
786
787 // Figure out which #pragma we're dealing with. The switch has no default
788 // because lex shouldn't emit the annotation token for unrecognized pragmas.
789 typedef bool (Parser::*PragmaHandler)(StringRef, SourceLocation);
790 PragmaHandler Handler = llvm::StringSwitch<PragmaHandler>(PragmaName)
791 .Case("data_seg", &Parser::HandlePragmaMSSegment)
792 .Case("bss_seg", &Parser::HandlePragmaMSSegment)
793 .Case("const_seg", &Parser::HandlePragmaMSSegment)
794 .Case("code_seg", &Parser::HandlePragmaMSSegment)
795 .Case("section", &Parser::HandlePragmaMSSection)
796 .Case("init_seg", &Parser::HandlePragmaMSInitSeg);
797
798 if (!(this->*Handler)(PragmaName, PragmaLocation)) {
799 // Pragma handling failed, and has been diagnosed. Slurp up the tokens
800 // until eof (really end of line) to prevent follow-on errors.
801 while (Tok.isNot(tok::eof))
802 PP.Lex(Tok);
803 PP.Lex(Tok);
804 }
805}
806
807bool Parser::HandlePragmaMSSection(StringRef PragmaName,
808 SourceLocation PragmaLocation) {
809 if (Tok.isNot(tok::l_paren)) {
810 PP.Diag(PragmaLocation, diag::warn_pragma_expected_lparen) << PragmaName;
811 return false;
812 }
813 PP.Lex(Tok); // (
814 // Parsing code for pragma section
815 if (Tok.isNot(tok::string_literal)) {
816 PP.Diag(PragmaLocation, diag::warn_pragma_expected_section_name)
817 << PragmaName;
818 return false;
819 }
820 ExprResult StringResult = ParseStringLiteralExpression();
821 if (StringResult.isInvalid())
822 return false; // Already diagnosed.
823 StringLiteral *SegmentName = cast<StringLiteral>(StringResult.get());
824 if (SegmentName->getCharByteWidth() != 1) {
825 PP.Diag(PragmaLocation, diag::warn_pragma_expected_non_wide_string)
826 << PragmaName;
827 return false;
828 }
829 int SectionFlags = ASTContext::PSF_Read;
830 bool SectionFlagsAreDefault = true;
831 while (Tok.is(tok::comma)) {
832 PP.Lex(Tok); // ,
833 // Ignore "long" and "short".
834 // They are undocumented, but widely used, section attributes which appear
835 // to do nothing.
836 if (Tok.is(tok::kw_long) || Tok.is(tok::kw_short)) {
837 PP.Lex(Tok); // long/short
838 continue;
839 }
840
841 if (!Tok.isAnyIdentifier()) {
842 PP.Diag(PragmaLocation, diag::warn_pragma_expected_action_or_r_paren)
843 << PragmaName;
844 return false;
845 }
846 ASTContext::PragmaSectionFlag Flag =
847 llvm::StringSwitch<ASTContext::PragmaSectionFlag>(
848 Tok.getIdentifierInfo()->getName())
849 .Case("read", ASTContext::PSF_Read)
850 .Case("write", ASTContext::PSF_Write)
851 .Case("execute", ASTContext::PSF_Execute)
852 .Case("shared", ASTContext::PSF_Invalid)
853 .Case("nopage", ASTContext::PSF_Invalid)
854 .Case("nocache", ASTContext::PSF_Invalid)
855 .Case("discard", ASTContext::PSF_Invalid)
856 .Case("remove", ASTContext::PSF_Invalid)
857 .Default(ASTContext::PSF_None);
858 if (Flag == ASTContext::PSF_None || Flag == ASTContext::PSF_Invalid) {
859 PP.Diag(PragmaLocation, Flag == ASTContext::PSF_None
860 ? diag::warn_pragma_invalid_specific_action
861 : diag::warn_pragma_unsupported_action)
862 << PragmaName << Tok.getIdentifierInfo()->getName();
863 return false;
864 }
865 SectionFlags |= Flag;
866 SectionFlagsAreDefault = false;
867 PP.Lex(Tok); // Identifier
868 }
869 // If no section attributes are specified, the section will be marked as
870 // read/write.
871 if (SectionFlagsAreDefault)
872 SectionFlags |= ASTContext::PSF_Write;
873 if (Tok.isNot(tok::r_paren)) {
874 PP.Diag(PragmaLocation, diag::warn_pragma_expected_rparen) << PragmaName;
875 return false;
876 }
877 PP.Lex(Tok); // )
878 if (Tok.isNot(tok::eof)) {
879 PP.Diag(PragmaLocation, diag::warn_pragma_extra_tokens_at_eol)
880 << PragmaName;
881 return false;
882 }
883 PP.Lex(Tok); // eof
884 Actions.ActOnPragmaMSSection(PragmaLocation, SectionFlags, SegmentName);
885 return true;
886}
887
888bool Parser::HandlePragmaMSSegment(StringRef PragmaName,
889 SourceLocation PragmaLocation) {
890 if (Tok.isNot(tok::l_paren)) {
891 PP.Diag(PragmaLocation, diag::warn_pragma_expected_lparen) << PragmaName;
892 return false;
893 }
894 PP.Lex(Tok); // (
895 Sema::PragmaMsStackAction Action = Sema::PSK_Reset;
896 StringRef SlotLabel;
897 if (Tok.isAnyIdentifier()) {
898 StringRef PushPop = Tok.getIdentifierInfo()->getName();
899 if (PushPop == "push")
900 Action = Sema::PSK_Push;
901 else if (PushPop == "pop")
902 Action = Sema::PSK_Pop;
903 else {
904 PP.Diag(PragmaLocation,
905 diag::warn_pragma_expected_section_push_pop_or_name)
906 << PragmaName;
907 return false;
908 }
909 if (Action != Sema::PSK_Reset) {
910 PP.Lex(Tok); // push | pop
911 if (Tok.is(tok::comma)) {
912 PP.Lex(Tok); // ,
913 // If we've got a comma, we either need a label or a string.
914 if (Tok.isAnyIdentifier()) {
915 SlotLabel = Tok.getIdentifierInfo()->getName();
916 PP.Lex(Tok); // identifier
917 if (Tok.is(tok::comma))
918 PP.Lex(Tok);
919 else if (Tok.isNot(tok::r_paren)) {
920 PP.Diag(PragmaLocation, diag::warn_pragma_expected_punc)
921 << PragmaName;
922 return false;
923 }
924 }
925 } else if (Tok.isNot(tok::r_paren)) {
926 PP.Diag(PragmaLocation, diag::warn_pragma_expected_punc) << PragmaName;
927 return false;
928 }
929 }
930 }
931 // Grab the string literal for our section name.
932 StringLiteral *SegmentName = nullptr;
933 if (Tok.isNot(tok::r_paren)) {
934 if (Tok.isNot(tok::string_literal)) {
935 unsigned DiagID = Action != Sema::PSK_Reset ? !SlotLabel.empty() ?
936 diag::warn_pragma_expected_section_name :
937 diag::warn_pragma_expected_section_label_or_name :
938 diag::warn_pragma_expected_section_push_pop_or_name;
939 PP.Diag(PragmaLocation, DiagID) << PragmaName;
940 return false;
941 }
942 ExprResult StringResult = ParseStringLiteralExpression();
943 if (StringResult.isInvalid())
944 return false; // Already diagnosed.
945 SegmentName = cast<StringLiteral>(StringResult.get());
946 if (SegmentName->getCharByteWidth() != 1) {
947 PP.Diag(PragmaLocation, diag::warn_pragma_expected_non_wide_string)
948 << PragmaName;
949 return false;
950 }
951 // Setting section "" has no effect
952 if (SegmentName->getLength())
953 Action = (Sema::PragmaMsStackAction)(Action | Sema::PSK_Set);
954 }
955 if (Tok.isNot(tok::r_paren)) {
956 PP.Diag(PragmaLocation, diag::warn_pragma_expected_rparen) << PragmaName;
957 return false;
958 }
959 PP.Lex(Tok); // )
960 if (Tok.isNot(tok::eof)) {
961 PP.Diag(PragmaLocation, diag::warn_pragma_extra_tokens_at_eol)
962 << PragmaName;
963 return false;
964 }
965 PP.Lex(Tok); // eof
966 Actions.ActOnPragmaMSSeg(PragmaLocation, Action, SlotLabel,
967 SegmentName, PragmaName);
968 return true;
969}
970
971// #pragma init_seg({ compiler | lib | user | "section-name" [, func-name]} )
972bool Parser::HandlePragmaMSInitSeg(StringRef PragmaName,
973 SourceLocation PragmaLocation) {
974 if (getTargetInfo().getTriple().getEnvironment() != llvm::Triple::MSVC) {
975 PP.Diag(PragmaLocation, diag::warn_pragma_init_seg_unsupported_target);
976 return false;
977 }
978
979 if (ExpectAndConsume(tok::l_paren, diag::warn_pragma_expected_lparen,
980 PragmaName))
981 return false;
982
983 // Parse either the known section names or the string section name.
984 StringLiteral *SegmentName = nullptr;
985 if (Tok.isAnyIdentifier()) {
986 auto *II = Tok.getIdentifierInfo();
987 StringRef Section = llvm::StringSwitch<StringRef>(II->getName())
988 .Case("compiler", "\".CRT$XCC\"")
989 .Case("lib", "\".CRT$XCL\"")
990 .Case("user", "\".CRT$XCU\"")
991 .Default("");
992
993 if (!Section.empty()) {
994 // Pretend the user wrote the appropriate string literal here.
995 Token Toks[1];
996 Toks[0].startToken();
997 Toks[0].setKind(tok::string_literal);
998 Toks[0].setLocation(Tok.getLocation());
999 Toks[0].setLiteralData(Section.data());
1000 Toks[0].setLength(Section.size());
1001 SegmentName =
1002 cast<StringLiteral>(Actions.ActOnStringLiteral(Toks, nullptr).get());
1003 PP.Lex(Tok);
1004 }
1005 } else if (Tok.is(tok::string_literal)) {
1006 ExprResult StringResult = ParseStringLiteralExpression();
1007 if (StringResult.isInvalid())
1008 return false;
1009 SegmentName = cast<StringLiteral>(StringResult.get());
1010 if (SegmentName->getCharByteWidth() != 1) {
1011 PP.Diag(PragmaLocation, diag::warn_pragma_expected_non_wide_string)
1012 << PragmaName;
1013 return false;
1014 }
1015 // FIXME: Add support for the '[, func-name]' part of the pragma.
1016 }
1017
1018 if (!SegmentName) {
1019 PP.Diag(PragmaLocation, diag::warn_pragma_expected_init_seg) << PragmaName;
1020 return false;
1021 }
1022
1023 if (ExpectAndConsume(tok::r_paren, diag::warn_pragma_expected_rparen,
1024 PragmaName) ||
1025 ExpectAndConsume(tok::eof, diag::warn_pragma_extra_tokens_at_eol,
1026 PragmaName))
1027 return false;
1028
1029 Actions.ActOnPragmaMSInitSeg(PragmaLocation, SegmentName);
1030 return true;
1031}

1033namespace {
1034struct PragmaLoopHintInfo {
1035 Token PragmaName;
1036 Token Option;
1037 ArrayRef<Token> Toks;
1038};
1039} // end anonymous namespace
1040
1041static std::string PragmaLoopHintString(Token PragmaName, Token Option) {
1042 std::string PragmaString;
1043 if (PragmaName.getIdentifierInfo()->getName() == "loop") {
1044 PragmaString = "clang loop ";
1045 PragmaString += Option.getIdentifierInfo()->getName();
1046 } else if (PragmaName.getIdentifierInfo()->getName() == "unroll_and_jam") {
1047 PragmaString = "unroll_and_jam";
1048 } else {
1049 assert(PragmaName.getIdentifierInfo()->getName() == "unroll" &&
1050 "Unexpected pragma name");
1051 PragmaString = "unroll";
1052 }
1053 return PragmaString;
1054}
1055
1056bool Parser::HandlePragmaLoopHint(LoopHint &Hint) {
1057 assert(Tok.is(tok::annot_pragma_loop_hint));
1058 PragmaLoopHintInfo *Info =
1059 static_cast<PragmaLoopHintInfo *>(Tok.getAnnotationValue());
1060
1061 IdentifierInfo *PragmaNameInfo = Info->PragmaName.getIdentifierInfo();
1062 Hint.PragmaNameLoc = IdentifierLoc::create(
1063 Actions.Context, Info->PragmaName.getLocation(), PragmaNameInfo);
1064
1065 // It is possible that the loop hint has no option identifier, such as
1066 // #pragma unroll(4).
1067 IdentifierInfo *OptionInfo = Info->Option.is(tok::identifier)
1068 ? Info->Option.getIdentifierInfo()
1069 : nullptr;
1070 Hint.OptionLoc = IdentifierLoc::create(
1071 Actions.Context, Info->Option.getLocation(), OptionInfo);
1072
1073 llvm::ArrayRef<Token> Toks = Info->Toks;
1074
1075 // Return a valid hint if pragma unroll or nounroll were specified
1076 // without an argument.
1077 bool PragmaUnroll = PragmaNameInfo->getName() == "unroll";
1078 bool PragmaNoUnroll = PragmaNameInfo->getName() == "nounroll";
1079 bool PragmaUnrollAndJam = PragmaNameInfo->getName() == "unroll_and_jam";
1080 bool PragmaNoUnrollAndJam = PragmaNameInfo->getName() == "nounroll_and_jam";
1081 if (Toks.empty() && (PragmaUnroll || PragmaNoUnroll || PragmaUnrollAndJam ||
1082 PragmaNoUnrollAndJam)) {
1083 ConsumeAnnotationToken();
1084 Hint.Range = Info->PragmaName.getLocation();
1085 return true;
1086 }
1087
1088 // The constant expression is always followed by an eof token, which increases
1089 // the TokSize by 1.
1090 assert(!Toks.empty() &&
1091 "PragmaLoopHintInfo::Toks must contain at least one token.");
1092
1093 // If no option is specified the argument is assumed to be a constant expr.
1094 bool OptionUnroll = false;
1095 bool OptionUnrollAndJam = false;
1096 bool OptionDistribute = false;
1097 bool OptionPipelineDisabled = false;
1098 bool StateOption = false;
1099 if (OptionInfo) { // Pragma Unroll does not specify an option.
1100 OptionUnroll = OptionInfo->isStr("unroll");
1101 OptionUnrollAndJam = OptionInfo->isStr("unroll_and_jam");
1102 OptionDistribute = OptionInfo->isStr("distribute");
1103 OptionPipelineDisabled = OptionInfo->isStr("pipeline");
1104 StateOption = llvm::StringSwitch<bool>(OptionInfo->getName())
1105 .Case("vectorize", true)
1106 .Case("interleave", true)
1107 .Default(false) ||
1108 OptionUnroll || OptionUnrollAndJam || OptionDistribute ||
1109 OptionPipelineDisabled;
1110 }
1111
1112 bool AssumeSafetyArg = !OptionUnroll && !OptionUnrollAndJam &&
1113 !OptionDistribute && !OptionPipelineDisabled;
1114 // Verify loop hint has an argument.
1115 if (Toks[0].is(tok::eof)) {
1116 ConsumeAnnotationToken();
1117 Diag(Toks[0].getLocation(), diag::err_pragma_loop_missing_argument)
1118 << /*StateArgument=*/StateOption
1119 << /*FullKeyword=*/(OptionUnroll || OptionUnrollAndJam)
1120 << /*AssumeSafetyKeyword=*/AssumeSafetyArg;
1121 return false;
1122 }
1123
1124 // Validate the argument.
1125 if (StateOption) {
1126 ConsumeAnnotationToken();
1127 SourceLocation StateLoc = Toks[0].getLocation();
1128 IdentifierInfo *StateInfo = Toks[0].getIdentifierInfo();
1129
1130 bool Valid = StateInfo &&
1131 llvm::StringSwitch<bool>(StateInfo->getName())
1132 .Case("disable", true)
1133 .Case("enable", !OptionPipelineDisabled)
1134 .Case("full", OptionUnroll || OptionUnrollAndJam)
1135 .Case("assume_safety", AssumeSafetyArg)
1136 .Default(false);
1137 if (!Valid) {
1138 if (OptionPipelineDisabled) {
1139 Diag(Toks[0].getLocation(), diag::err_pragma_pipeline_invalid_keyword);
1140 } else {
1141 Diag(Toks[0].getLocation(), diag::err_pragma_invalid_keyword)
1142 << /*FullKeyword=*/(OptionUnroll || OptionUnrollAndJam)
1143 << /*AssumeSafetyKeyword=*/AssumeSafetyArg;
1144 }
1145 return false;
1146 }
1147 if (Toks.size() > 2)
1148 Diag(Tok.getLocation(), diag::warn_pragma_extra_tokens_at_eol)
1149 << PragmaLoopHintString(Info->PragmaName, Info->Option);
1150 Hint.StateLoc = IdentifierLoc::create(Actions.Context, StateLoc, StateInfo);
1151 } else {
1152 // Enter constant expression including eof terminator into token stream.
1153 PP.EnterTokenStream(Toks, /*DisableMacroExpansion=*/false,
1154 /*IsReinject=*/false);
1155 ConsumeAnnotationToken();
1156
1157 ExprResult R = ParseConstantExpression();
1158
1159 // Tokens following an error in an ill-formed constant expression will
1160 // remain in the token stream and must be removed.
1161 if (Tok.isNot(tok::eof)) {
1162 Diag(Tok.getLocation(), diag::warn_pragma_extra_tokens_at_eol)
1163 << PragmaLoopHintString(Info->PragmaName, Info->Option);
1164 while (Tok.isNot(tok::eof))
1165 ConsumeAnyToken();
1166 }
1167
1168 ConsumeToken(); // Consume the constant expression eof terminator.
1169
1170 if (R.isInvalid() ||
1171 Actions.CheckLoopHintExpr(R.get(), Toks[0].getLocation()))
1172 return false;
1173
1174 // Argument is a constant expression with an integer type.
1175 Hint.ValueExpr = R.get();
1176 }
1177
1178 Hint.Range = SourceRange(Info->PragmaName.getLocation(),
1179 Info->Toks.back().getLocation());
1180 return true;
1181}

1198static StringRef getIdentifier(const Token &Tok) {
1199 if (Tok.is(tok::identifier))
1200 return Tok.getIdentifierInfo()->getName();
1201 const char *S = tok::getKeywordSpelling(Tok.getKind());
1202 if (!S)
1203 return "";

1207static bool isAbstractAttrMatcherRule(attr::SubjectMatchRule Rule) {
1208 using namespace attr;
1209 switch (Rule) {
1210#define ATTR_MATCH_RULE(Value, Spelling, IsAbstract) \
1211 case Value: \
1212 return IsAbstract;
1213#include "clang/Basic/AttrSubMatchRulesList.inc"
1214 }
1215 llvm_unreachable("Invalid attribute subject match rule");
1216 return false;
1217}

1219static void diagnoseExpectedAttributeSubjectSubRule(
1220 Parser &PRef, attr::SubjectMatchRule PrimaryRule, StringRef PrimaryRuleName,
1221 SourceLocation SubRuleLoc) {
1222 auto Diagnostic =
1223 PRef.Diag(SubRuleLoc,
1224 diag::err_pragma_attribute_expected_subject_sub_identifier)
1225 << PrimaryRuleName;
1226 if (const char *SubRules = validAttributeSubjectMatchSubRules(PrimaryRule))
1227 Diagnostic << /*SubRulesSupported=*/1 << SubRules;
1228 else
1229 Diagnostic << /*SubRulesSupported=*/0;
1230}

1232static void diagnoseUnknownAttributeSubjectSubRule(
1233 Parser &PRef, attr::SubjectMatchRule PrimaryRule, StringRef PrimaryRuleName,
1234 StringRef SubRuleName, SourceLocation SubRuleLoc) {
1235
1236 auto Diagnostic =
1237 PRef.Diag(SubRuleLoc, diag::err_pragma_attribute_unknown_subject_sub_rule)
1238 << SubRuleName << PrimaryRuleName;
1239 if (const char *SubRules = validAttributeSubjectMatchSubRules(PrimaryRule))
1240 Diagnostic << /*SubRulesSupported=*/1 << SubRules;
1241 else
1242 Diagnostic << /*SubRulesSupported=*/0;
1243}
1244
1245bool Parser::ParsePragmaAttributeSubjectMatchRuleSet(
1246 attr::ParsedSubjectMatchRuleSet &SubjectMatchRules, SourceLocation &AnyLoc,
1247 SourceLocation &LastMatchRuleEndLoc) {
1248 bool IsAny = false;
1249 BalancedDelimiterTracker AnyParens(*this, tok::l_paren);
1250 if (getIdentifier(Tok) == "any") {
1251 AnyLoc = ConsumeToken();
1252 IsAny = true;
1253 if (AnyParens.expectAndConsume())
1254 return true;
1255 }
1256
1257 do {
1258 // Parse the subject matcher rule.
1259 StringRef Name = getIdentifier(Tok);
1260 if (Name.empty()) {
1261 Diag(Tok, diag::err_pragma_attribute_expected_subject_identifier);
1262 return true;
1263 }
1264 std::pair<Optional<attr::SubjectMatchRule>,
1265 Optional<attr::SubjectMatchRule> (*)(StringRef, bool)>
1266 Rule = isAttributeSubjectMatchRule(Name);
1267 if (!Rule.first) {
1268 Diag(Tok, diag::err_pragma_attribute_unknown_subject_rule) << Name;
1269 return true;
1270 }
1271 attr::SubjectMatchRule PrimaryRule = *Rule.first;
1272 SourceLocation RuleLoc = ConsumeToken();
1273
1274 BalancedDelimiterTracker Parens(*this, tok::l_paren);
1275 if (isAbstractAttrMatcherRule(PrimaryRule)) {
1276 if (Parens.expectAndConsume())
1277 return true;
1278 } else if (Parens.consumeOpen()) {
1279 if (!SubjectMatchRules
1280 .insert(
1281 std::make_pair(PrimaryRule, SourceRange(RuleLoc, RuleLoc)))
1282 .second)
1283 Diag(RuleLoc, diag::err_pragma_attribute_duplicate_subject)
1284 << Name
1285 << FixItHint::CreateRemoval(SourceRange(
1286 RuleLoc, Tok.is(tok::comma) ? Tok.getLocation() : RuleLoc));
1287 LastMatchRuleEndLoc = RuleLoc;
1288 continue;
1289 }
1290
1291 // Parse the sub-rules.
1292 StringRef SubRuleName = getIdentifier(Tok);
1293 if (SubRuleName.empty()) {
1294 diagnoseExpectedAttributeSubjectSubRule(*this, PrimaryRule, Name,
1295 Tok.getLocation());
1296 return true;
1297 }
1298 attr::SubjectMatchRule SubRule;
1299 if (SubRuleName == "unless") {
1300 SourceLocation SubRuleLoc = ConsumeToken();
1301 BalancedDelimiterTracker Parens(*this, tok::l_paren);
1302 if (Parens.expectAndConsume())
1303 return true;
1304 SubRuleName = getIdentifier(Tok);
1305 if (SubRuleName.empty()) {
1306 diagnoseExpectedAttributeSubjectSubRule(*this, PrimaryRule, Name,
1307 SubRuleLoc);
1308 return true;
1309 }
1310 auto SubRuleOrNone = Rule.second(SubRuleName, /*IsUnless=*/true);
1311 if (!SubRuleOrNone) {
1312 std::string SubRuleUnlessName = "unless(" + SubRuleName.str() + ")";
1313 diagnoseUnknownAttributeSubjectSubRule(*this, PrimaryRule, Name,
1314 SubRuleUnlessName, SubRuleLoc);
1315 return true;
1316 }
1317 SubRule = *SubRuleOrNone;
1318 ConsumeToken();
1319 if (Parens.consumeClose())
1320 return true;
1321 } else {
1322 auto SubRuleOrNone = Rule.second(SubRuleName, /*IsUnless=*/false);
1323 if (!SubRuleOrNone) {
1324 diagnoseUnknownAttributeSubjectSubRule(*this, PrimaryRule, Name,
1325 SubRuleName, Tok.getLocation());
1326 return true;
1327 }
1328 SubRule = *SubRuleOrNone;
1329 ConsumeToken();
1330 }
1331 SourceLocation RuleEndLoc = Tok.getLocation();
1332 LastMatchRuleEndLoc = RuleEndLoc;
1333 if (Parens.consumeClose())
1334 return true;
1335 if (!SubjectMatchRules
1336 .insert(std::make_pair(SubRule, SourceRange(RuleLoc, RuleEndLoc)))
1337 .second) {
1338 Diag(RuleLoc, diag::err_pragma_attribute_duplicate_subject)
1339 << attr::getSubjectMatchRuleSpelling(SubRule)
1340 << FixItHint::CreateRemoval(SourceRange(
1341 RuleLoc, Tok.is(tok::comma) ? Tok.getLocation() : RuleEndLoc));
1342 continue;
1343 }
1344 } while (IsAny && TryConsumeToken(tok::comma));
1345
1346 if (IsAny)
1347 if (AnyParens.consumeClose())
1348 return true;
1349
1350 return false;
1351}

1353namespace {
1354
1355/// Describes the stage at which attribute subject rule parsing was interrupted.
1356enum class MissingAttributeSubjectRulesRecoveryPoint {
1357 Comma,
1358 ApplyTo,
1359 Equals,
1360 Any,
1361 None,
1362};
1363
1364MissingAttributeSubjectRulesRecoveryPoint
1365getAttributeSubjectRulesRecoveryPointForToken(const Token &Tok) {
1366 if (const auto *II = Tok.getIdentifierInfo()) {
1367 if (II->isStr("apply_to"))
1368 return MissingAttributeSubjectRulesRecoveryPoint::ApplyTo;
1369 if (II->isStr("any"))
1370 return MissingAttributeSubjectRulesRecoveryPoint::Any;
1371 }
1372 if (Tok.is(tok::equal))
1373 return MissingAttributeSubjectRulesRecoveryPoint::Equals;
1374 return MissingAttributeSubjectRulesRecoveryPoint::None;
1375}
1376
1377/// Creates a diagnostic for the attribute subject rule parsing diagnostic that
1378/// suggests the possible attribute subject rules in a fix-it together with
1379/// any other missing tokens.
1380DiagnosticBuilder createExpectedAttributeSubjectRulesTokenDiagnostic(
1381 unsigned DiagID, ParsedAttr &Attribute,
1382 MissingAttributeSubjectRulesRecoveryPoint Point, Parser &PRef) {
1383 SourceLocation Loc = PRef.getEndOfPreviousToken();
1384 if (Loc.isInvalid())
1385 Loc = PRef.getCurToken().getLocation();
1386 auto Diagnostic = PRef.Diag(Loc, DiagID);
1387 std::string FixIt;
1388 MissingAttributeSubjectRulesRecoveryPoint EndPoint =
1389 getAttributeSubjectRulesRecoveryPointForToken(PRef.getCurToken());
1390 if (Point == MissingAttributeSubjectRulesRecoveryPoint::Comma)
1391 FixIt = ", ";
1392 if (Point <= MissingAttributeSubjectRulesRecoveryPoint::ApplyTo &&
1393 EndPoint > MissingAttributeSubjectRulesRecoveryPoint::ApplyTo)
1394 FixIt += "apply_to";
1395 if (Point <= MissingAttributeSubjectRulesRecoveryPoint::Equals &&
1396 EndPoint > MissingAttributeSubjectRulesRecoveryPoint::Equals)
1397 FixIt += " = ";
1398 SourceRange FixItRange(Loc);
1399 if (EndPoint == MissingAttributeSubjectRulesRecoveryPoint::None) {
1400 // Gather the subject match rules that are supported by the attribute.
1401 SmallVector<std::pair<attr::SubjectMatchRule, bool>, 4> SubjectMatchRuleSet;
1402 Attribute.getMatchRules(PRef.getLangOpts(), SubjectMatchRuleSet);
1403 if (SubjectMatchRuleSet.empty()) {
1404 // FIXME: We can emit a "fix-it" with a subject list placeholder when
1405 // placeholders will be supported by the fix-its.
1406 return Diagnostic;
1407 }
1408 FixIt += "any(";
1409 bool NeedsComma = false;
1410 for (const auto &I : SubjectMatchRuleSet) {
1411 // Ensure that the missing rule is reported in the fix-it only when it's
1412 // supported in the current language mode.
1413 if (!I.second)
1414 continue;
1415 if (NeedsComma)
1416 FixIt += ", ";
1417 else
1418 NeedsComma = true;
1419 FixIt += attr::getSubjectMatchRuleSpelling(I.first);
1420 }
1421 FixIt += ")";
1422 // Check if we need to remove the range
1423 PRef.SkipUntil(tok::eof, Parser::StopBeforeMatch);
1424 FixItRange.setEnd(PRef.getCurToken().getLocation());
1425 }
1426 if (FixItRange.getBegin() == FixItRange.getEnd())
1427 Diagnostic << FixItHint::CreateInsertion(FixItRange.getBegin(), FixIt);
1428 else
1429 Diagnostic << FixItHint::CreateReplacement(
1430 CharSourceRange::getCharRange(FixItRange), FixIt);
1431 return Diagnostic;
1432}
1433
1434} // end anonymous namespace
1435
1436void Parser::HandlePragmaAttribute() {
1437 assert(Tok.is(tok::annot_pragma_attribute) &&
1438 "Expected #pragma attribute annotation token");
1439 SourceLocation PragmaLoc = Tok.getLocation();
1440 auto *Info = static_cast<PragmaAttributeInfo *>(Tok.getAnnotationValue());
1441 if (Info->Action == PragmaAttributeInfo::Pop) {
1442 ConsumeAnnotationToken();
1443 Actions.ActOnPragmaAttributePop(PragmaLoc, Info->Namespace);
1444 return;
1445 }
1446 // Parse the actual attribute with its arguments.
1447 assert((Info->Action == PragmaAttributeInfo::Push ||
1448 Info->Action == PragmaAttributeInfo::Attribute) &&
1449 "Unexpected #pragma attribute command");
1450
1451 if (Info->Action == PragmaAttributeInfo::Push && Info->Tokens.empty()) {
1452 ConsumeAnnotationToken();
1453 Actions.ActOnPragmaAttributeEmptyPush(PragmaLoc, Info->Namespace);
1454 return;
1455 }
1456
1457 PP.EnterTokenStream(Info->Tokens, /*DisableMacroExpansion=*/false,
1458 /*IsReinject=*/false);
1459 ConsumeAnnotationToken();
1460
1461 ParsedAttributes &Attrs = Info->Attributes;
1462 Attrs.clearListOnly();
1463
1464 auto SkipToEnd = [this]() {
1465 SkipUntil(tok::eof, StopBeforeMatch);
1466 ConsumeToken();
1467 };
1468
1469 if (Tok.is(tok::l_square) && NextToken().is(tok::l_square)) {
1470 // Parse the CXX11 style attribute.
1471 ParseCXX11AttributeSpecifier(Attrs);
1472 } else if (Tok.is(tok::kw___attribute)) {
1473 ConsumeToken();
1474 if (ExpectAndConsume(tok::l_paren, diag::err_expected_lparen_after,
1475 "attribute"))
1476 return SkipToEnd();
1477 if (ExpectAndConsume(tok::l_paren, diag::err_expected_lparen_after, "("))
1478 return SkipToEnd();
1479
1480 if (Tok.isNot(tok::identifier)) {
1481 Diag(Tok, diag::err_pragma_attribute_expected_attribute_name);
1482 SkipToEnd();
1483 return;
1484 }
1485 IdentifierInfo *AttrName = Tok.getIdentifierInfo();
1486 SourceLocation AttrNameLoc = ConsumeToken();
1487
1488 if (Tok.isNot(tok::l_paren))
1489 Attrs.addNew(AttrName, AttrNameLoc, nullptr, AttrNameLoc, nullptr, 0,
1490 ParsedAttr::AS_GNU);
1491 else
1492 ParseGNUAttributeArgs(AttrName, AttrNameLoc, Attrs, /*EndLoc=*/nullptr,
1493 /*ScopeName=*/nullptr,
1494 /*ScopeLoc=*/SourceLocation(), ParsedAttr::AS_GNU,
1495 /*Declarator=*/nullptr);
1496
1497 if (ExpectAndConsume(tok::r_paren))
1498 return SkipToEnd();
1499 if (ExpectAndConsume(tok::r_paren))
1500 return SkipToEnd();
1501 } else if (Tok.is(tok::kw___declspec)) {
1502 ParseMicrosoftDeclSpecs(Attrs);
1503 } else {
1504 Diag(Tok, diag::err_pragma_attribute_expected_attribute_syntax);
1505 if (Tok.getIdentifierInfo()) {
1506 // If we suspect that this is an attribute suggest the use of
1507 // '__attribute__'.
1508 if (ParsedAttr::getKind(Tok.getIdentifierInfo(), /*ScopeName=*/nullptr,
1509 ParsedAttr::AS_GNU) !=
1510 ParsedAttr::UnknownAttribute) {
1511 SourceLocation InsertStartLoc = Tok.getLocation();
1512 ConsumeToken();
1513 if (Tok.is(tok::l_paren)) {
1514 ConsumeAnyToken();
1515 SkipUntil(tok::r_paren, StopBeforeMatch);
1516 if (Tok.isNot(tok::r_paren))
1517 return SkipToEnd();
1518 }
1519 Diag(Tok, diag::note_pragma_attribute_use_attribute_kw)
1520 << FixItHint::CreateInsertion(InsertStartLoc, "__attribute__((")
1521 << FixItHint::CreateInsertion(Tok.getEndLoc(), "))");
1522 }
1523 }
1524 SkipToEnd();
1525 return;
1526 }
1527
1528 if (Attrs.empty() || Attrs.begin()->isInvalid()) {
1529 SkipToEnd();
1530 return;
1531 }
1532
1533 // Ensure that we don't have more than one attribute.
1534 if (Attrs.size() > 1) {
1535 SourceLocation Loc = Attrs[1].getLoc();
1536 Diag(Loc, diag::err_pragma_attribute_multiple_attributes);
1537 SkipToEnd();
1538 return;
1539 }
1540
1541 ParsedAttr &Attribute = *Attrs.begin();
1542 if (!Attribute.isSupportedByPragmaAttribute()) {
1543 Diag(PragmaLoc, diag::err_pragma_attribute_unsupported_attribute)
1544 << Attribute.getName();
1545 SkipToEnd();
1546 return;
1547 }
1548
1549 // Parse the subject-list.
1550 if (!TryConsumeToken(tok::comma)) {
1551 createExpectedAttributeSubjectRulesTokenDiagnostic(
1552 diag::err_expected, Attribute,
1553 MissingAttributeSubjectRulesRecoveryPoint::Comma, *this)
1554 << tok::comma;
1555 SkipToEnd();
1556 return;
1557 }
1558
1559 if (Tok.isNot(tok::identifier)) {
1560 createExpectedAttributeSubjectRulesTokenDiagnostic(
1561 diag::err_pragma_attribute_invalid_subject_set_specifier, Attribute,
1562 MissingAttributeSubjectRulesRecoveryPoint::ApplyTo, *this);
1563 SkipToEnd();
1564 return;
1565 }
1566 const IdentifierInfo *II = Tok.getIdentifierInfo();
1567 if (!II->isStr("apply_to")) {
1568 createExpectedAttributeSubjectRulesTokenDiagnostic(
1569 diag::err_pragma_attribute_invalid_subject_set_specifier, Attribute,
1570 MissingAttributeSubjectRulesRecoveryPoint::ApplyTo, *this);
1571 SkipToEnd();
1572 return;
1573 }
1574 ConsumeToken();
1575
1576 if (!TryConsumeToken(tok::equal)) {
1577 createExpectedAttributeSubjectRulesTokenDiagnostic(
1578 diag::err_expected, Attribute,
1579 MissingAttributeSubjectRulesRecoveryPoint::Equals, *this)
1580 << tok::equal;
1581 SkipToEnd();
1582 return;
1583 }
1584
1585 attr::ParsedSubjectMatchRuleSet SubjectMatchRules;
1586 SourceLocation AnyLoc, LastMatchRuleEndLoc;
1587 if (ParsePragmaAttributeSubjectMatchRuleSet(SubjectMatchRules, AnyLoc,
1588 LastMatchRuleEndLoc)) {
1589 SkipToEnd();
1590 return;
1591 }
1592
1593 // Tokens following an ill-formed attribute will remain in the token stream
1594 // and must be removed.
1595 if (Tok.isNot(tok::eof)) {
1596 Diag(Tok, diag::err_pragma_attribute_extra_tokens_after_attribute);
1597 SkipToEnd();
1598 return;
1599 }
1600
1601 // Consume the eof terminator token.
1602 ConsumeToken();
1603
1604 // Handle a mixed push/attribute by desurging to a push, then an attribute.
1605 if (Info->Action == PragmaAttributeInfo::Push)
1606 Actions.ActOnPragmaAttributeEmptyPush(PragmaLoc, Info->Namespace);
1607
1608 Actions.ActOnPragmaAttributeAttribute(Attribute, PragmaLoc,
1609 std::move(SubjectMatchRules));
1610}

1612// #pragma GCC visibility comes in two variants:
1613// 'push' '(' [visibility] ')'
1614// 'pop'
1615void PragmaGCCVisibilityHandler::HandlePragma(Preprocessor &PP,
1616 PragmaIntroducer Introducer,
1617 Token &VisTok) {
1618 SourceLocation VisLoc = VisTok.getLocation();
1619
1620 Token Tok;
1621 PP.LexUnexpandedToken(Tok);
1622
1623 const IdentifierInfo *PushPop = Tok.getIdentifierInfo();
1624
1625 const IdentifierInfo *VisType;
1626 if (PushPop && PushPop->isStr("pop")) {
1627 VisType = nullptr;
1628 } else if (PushPop && PushPop->isStr("push")) {
1629 PP.LexUnexpandedToken(Tok);
1630 if (Tok.isNot(tok::l_paren)) {
1631 PP.Diag(Tok.getLocation(), diag::warn_pragma_expected_lparen)
1632 << "visibility";
1633 return;
1634 }
1635 PP.LexUnexpandedToken(Tok);
1636 VisType = Tok.getIdentifierInfo();
1637 if (!VisType) {
1638 PP.Diag(Tok.getLocation(), diag::warn_pragma_expected_identifier)
1639 << "visibility";
1640 return;
1641 }
1642 PP.LexUnexpandedToken(Tok);
1643 if (Tok.isNot(tok::r_paren)) {
1644 PP.Diag(Tok.getLocation(), diag::warn_pragma_expected_rparen)
1645 << "visibility";
1646 return;
1647 }
1648 } else {
1649 PP.Diag(Tok.getLocation(), diag::warn_pragma_expected_identifier)
1650 << "visibility";
1651 return;
1652 }
1653 SourceLocation EndLoc = Tok.getLocation();
1654 PP.LexUnexpandedToken(Tok);
1655 if (Tok.isNot(tok::eod)) {
1656 PP.Diag(Tok.getLocation(), diag::warn_pragma_extra_tokens_at_eol)
1657 << "visibility";
1658 return;
1659 }
1660
1661 auto Toks = llvm::make_unique<Token[]>(1);
1662 Toks[0].startToken();
1663 Toks[0].setKind(tok::annot_pragma_vis);
1664 Toks[0].setLocation(VisLoc);
1665 Toks[0].setAnnotationEndLoc(EndLoc);
1666 Toks[0].setAnnotationValue(
1667 const_cast<void *>(static_cast<const void *>(VisType)));
1668 PP.EnterTokenStream(std::move(Toks), 1, /*DisableMacroExpansion=*/true,
1669 /*IsReinject=*/false);
1670}
1671
1672// #pragma pack(...) comes in the following delicious flavors:
1673// pack '(' [integer] ')'
1674// pack '(' 'show' ')'
1675// pack '(' ('push' | 'pop') [',' identifier] [, integer] ')'
1676void PragmaPackHandler::HandlePragma(Preprocessor &PP,
1677 PragmaIntroducer Introducer,
1678 Token &PackTok) {
1679 SourceLocation PackLoc = PackTok.getLocation();
1680
1681 Token Tok;
1682 PP.Lex(Tok);
1683 if (Tok.isNot(tok::l_paren)) {
1684 PP.Diag(Tok.getLocation(), diag::warn_pragma_expected_lparen) << "pack";
1685 return;
1686 }
1687
1688 Sema::PragmaMsStackAction Action = Sema::PSK_Reset;
1689 StringRef SlotLabel;
1690 Token Alignment;
1691 Alignment.startToken();
1692 PP.Lex(Tok);
1693 if (Tok.is(tok::numeric_constant)) {
1694 Alignment = Tok;
1695
1696 PP.Lex(Tok);
1697
1698 // In MSVC/gcc, #pragma pack(4) sets the alignment without affecting
1699 // the push/pop stack.
1700 // In Apple gcc, #pragma pack(4) is equivalent to #pragma pack(push, 4)
1701 Action =
1702 PP.getLangOpts().ApplePragmaPack ? Sema::PSK_Push_Set : Sema::PSK_Set;
1703 } else if (Tok.is(tok::identifier)) {
1704 const IdentifierInfo *II = Tok.getIdentifierInfo();
1705 if (II->isStr("show")) {
1706 Action = Sema::PSK_Show;
1707 PP.Lex(Tok);
1708 } else {
1709 if (II->isStr("push")) {
1710 Action = Sema::PSK_Push;
1711 } else if (II->isStr("pop")) {
1712 Action = Sema::PSK_Pop;
1713 } else {
1714 PP.Diag(Tok.getLocation(), diag::warn_pragma_invalid_action) << "pack";
1715 return;
1716 }
1717 PP.Lex(Tok);
1718
1719 if (Tok.is(tok::comma)) {
1720 PP.Lex(Tok);
1721
1722 if (Tok.is(tok::numeric_constant)) {
1723 Action = (Sema::PragmaMsStackAction)(Action | Sema::PSK_Set);
1724 Alignment = Tok;
1725
1726 PP.Lex(Tok);
1727 } else if (Tok.is(tok::identifier)) {
1728 SlotLabel = Tok.getIdentifierInfo()->getName();
1729 PP.Lex(Tok);
1730
1731 if (Tok.is(tok::comma)) {
1732 PP.Lex(Tok);
1733
1734 if (Tok.isNot(tok::numeric_constant)) {
1735 PP.Diag(Tok.getLocation(), diag::warn_pragma_pack_malformed);
1736 return;
1737 }
1738
1739 Action = (Sema::PragmaMsStackAction)(Action | Sema::PSK_Set);
1740 Alignment = Tok;
1741
1742 PP.Lex(Tok);
1743 }
1744 } else {
1745 PP.Diag(Tok.getLocation(), diag::warn_pragma_pack_malformed);
1746 return;
1747 }
1748 }
1749 }
1750 } else if (PP.getLangOpts().ApplePragmaPack) {
1751 // In MSVC/gcc, #pragma pack() resets the alignment without affecting
1752 // the push/pop stack.
1753 // In Apple gcc #pragma pack() is equivalent to #pragma pack(pop).
1754 Action = Sema::PSK_Pop;
1755 }
1756
1757 if (Tok.isNot(tok::r_paren)) {
1758 PP.Diag(Tok.getLocation(), diag::warn_pragma_expected_rparen) << "pack";
1759 return;
1760 }
1761
1762 SourceLocation RParenLoc = Tok.getLocation();
1763 PP.Lex(Tok);
1764 if (Tok.isNot(tok::eod)) {
1765 PP.Diag(Tok.getLocation(), diag::warn_pragma_extra_tokens_at_eol) << "pack";
1766 return;
1767 }
1768
1769 PragmaPackInfo *Info =
1770 PP.getPreprocessorAllocator().Allocate<PragmaPackInfo>(1);
1771 Info->Action = Action;
1772 Info->SlotLabel = SlotLabel;
1773 Info->Alignment = Alignment;
1774
1775 MutableArrayRef<Token> Toks(PP.getPreprocessorAllocator().Allocate<Token>(1),
1776 1);
1777 Toks[0].startToken();
1778 Toks[0].setKind(tok::annot_pragma_pack);
1779 Toks[0].setLocation(PackLoc);
1780 Toks[0].setAnnotationEndLoc(RParenLoc);
1781 Toks[0].setAnnotationValue(static_cast<void*>(Info));
1782 PP.EnterTokenStream(Toks, /*DisableMacroExpansion=*/true,
1783 /*IsReinject=*/false);
1784}

1786// #pragma ms_struct on
1787// #pragma ms_struct off
1788void PragmaMSStructHandler::HandlePragma(Preprocessor &PP,
1789 PragmaIntroducer Introducer,
1790 Token &MSStructTok) {
1791 PragmaMSStructKind Kind = PMSST_OFF;
1792
1793 Token Tok;
1794 PP.Lex(Tok);
1795 if (Tok.isNot(tok::identifier)) {
1796 PP.Diag(Tok.getLocation(), diag::warn_pragma_ms_struct);
1797 return;
1798 }
1799 SourceLocation EndLoc = Tok.getLocation();
1800 const IdentifierInfo *II = Tok.getIdentifierInfo();
1801 if (II->isStr("on")) {
1802 Kind = PMSST_ON;
1803 PP.Lex(Tok);
1804 }
1805 else if (II->isStr("off") || II->isStr("reset"))
1806 PP.Lex(Tok);
1807 else {
1808 PP.Diag(Tok.getLocation(), diag::warn_pragma_ms_struct);
1809 return;
1810 }
1811
1812 if (Tok.isNot(tok::eod)) {
1813 PP.Diag(Tok.getLocation(), diag::warn_pragma_extra_tokens_at_eol)
1814 << "ms_struct";
1815 return;
1816 }
1817
1818 MutableArrayRef<Token> Toks(PP.getPreprocessorAllocator().Allocate<Token>(1),
1819 1);
1820 Toks[0].startToken();
1821 Toks[0].setKind(tok::annot_pragma_msstruct);
1822 Toks[0].setLocation(MSStructTok.getLocation());
1823 Toks[0].setAnnotationEndLoc(EndLoc);
1824 Toks[0].setAnnotationValue(reinterpret_cast<void*>(
1825 static_cast<uintptr_t>(Kind)));
1826 PP.EnterTokenStream(Toks, /*DisableMacroExpansion=*/true,
1827 /*IsReinject=*/false);
1828}

1830// #pragma clang section bss="abc" data="" rodata="def" text=""
1831void PragmaClangSectionHandler::HandlePragma(Preprocessor &PP,
1832 PragmaIntroducer Introducer,
1833 Token &FirstToken) {
1834
1835 Token Tok;
1836 auto SecKind = Sema::PragmaClangSectionKind::PCSK_Invalid;
1837
1838 PP.Lex(Tok); // eat 'section'
1839 while (Tok.isNot(tok::eod)) {
1840 if (Tok.isNot(tok::identifier)) {
1841 PP.Diag(Tok.getLocation(), diag::err_pragma_expected_clang_section_name) << "clang section";
1842 return;
1843 }
1844
1845 const IdentifierInfo *SecType = Tok.getIdentifierInfo();
1846 if (SecType->isStr("bss"))
1847 SecKind = Sema::PragmaClangSectionKind::PCSK_BSS;
1848 else if (SecType->isStr("data"))
1849 SecKind = Sema::PragmaClangSectionKind::PCSK_Data;
1850 else if (SecType->isStr("rodata"))
1851 SecKind = Sema::PragmaClangSectionKind::PCSK_Rodata;
1852 else if (SecType->isStr("text"))
1853 SecKind = Sema::PragmaClangSectionKind::PCSK_Text;
1854 else {
1855 PP.Diag(Tok.getLocation(), diag::err_pragma_expected_clang_section_name) << "clang section";
1856 return;
1857 }
1858
1859 PP.Lex(Tok); // eat ['bss'|'data'|'rodata'|'text']
1860 if (Tok.isNot(tok::equal)) {
1861 PP.Diag(Tok.getLocation(), diag::err_pragma_clang_section_expected_equal) << SecKind;
1862 return;
1863 }
1864
1865 std::string SecName;
1866 if (!PP.LexStringLiteral(Tok, SecName, "pragma clang section", false))
1867 return;
1868
1869 Actions.ActOnPragmaClangSection(Tok.getLocation(),
1870 (SecName.size()? Sema::PragmaClangSectionAction::PCSA_Set :
1871 Sema::PragmaClangSectionAction::PCSA_Clear),
1872 SecKind, SecName);
1873 }
1874}
1875
1876// #pragma 'align' '=' {'native','natural','mac68k','power','reset'}
1877// #pragma 'options 'align' '=' {'native','natural','mac68k','power','reset'}
1878static void ParseAlignPragma(Preprocessor &PP, Token &FirstTok,
1879 bool IsOptions) {
1880 Token Tok;
1881
1882 if (IsOptions) {
1883 PP.Lex(Tok);
1884 if (Tok.isNot(tok::identifier) ||
1885 !Tok.getIdentifierInfo()->isStr("align")) {
1886 PP.Diag(Tok.getLocation(), diag::warn_pragma_options_expected_align);
1887 return;
1888 }
1889 }
1890
1891 PP.Lex(Tok);
1892 if (Tok.isNot(tok::equal)) {
1893 PP.Diag(Tok.getLocation(), diag::warn_pragma_align_expected_equal)
1894 << IsOptions;
1895 return;
1896 }
1897
1898 PP.Lex(Tok);
1899 if (Tok.isNot(tok::identifier)) {
1900 PP.Diag(Tok.getLocation(), diag::warn_pragma_expected_identifier)
1901 << (IsOptions ? "options" : "align");
1902 return;
1903 }
1904
1905 Sema::PragmaOptionsAlignKind Kind = Sema::POAK_Natural;
1906 const IdentifierInfo *II = Tok.getIdentifierInfo();
1907 if (II->isStr("native"))
1908 Kind = Sema::POAK_Native;
1909 else if (II->isStr("natural"))
1910 Kind = Sema::POAK_Natural;
1911 else if (II->isStr("packed"))
1912 Kind = Sema::POAK_Packed;
1913 else if (II->isStr("power"))
1914 Kind = Sema::POAK_Power;
1915 else if (II->isStr("mac68k"))
1916 Kind = Sema::POAK_Mac68k;
1917 else if (II->isStr("reset"))
1918 Kind = Sema::POAK_Reset;
1919 else {
1920 PP.Diag(Tok.getLocation(), diag::warn_pragma_align_invalid_option)
1921 << IsOptions;
1922 return;
1923 }
1924
1925 SourceLocation EndLoc = Tok.getLocation();
1926 PP.Lex(Tok);
1927 if (Tok.isNot(tok::eod)) {
1928 PP.Diag(Tok.getLocation(), diag::warn_pragma_extra_tokens_at_eol)
1929 << (IsOptions ? "options" : "align");
1930 return;
1931 }
1932
1933 MutableArrayRef<Token> Toks(PP.getPreprocessorAllocator().Allocate<Token>(1),

1942 /*IsReinject=*/false);

1957// #pragma unused(identifier)
1958void PragmaUnusedHandler::HandlePragma(Preprocessor &PP,
1959 PragmaIntroducer Introducer,
1960 Token &UnusedTok) {
1961 // FIXME: Should we be expanding macros here? My guess is no.
1962 SourceLocation UnusedLoc = UnusedTok.getLocation();
1963
1964 // Lex the left '('.
1965 Token Tok;
1966 PP.Lex(Tok);
1967 if (Tok.isNot(tok::l_paren)) {
1968 PP.Diag(Tok.getLocation(), diag::warn_pragma_expected_lparen) << "unused";
1969 return;
1970 }
1971
1972 // Lex the declaration reference(s).
1973 SmallVector<Token, 5> Identifiers;
1974 SourceLocation RParenLoc;
1975 bool LexID = true;
1976
1977 while (true) {
1978 PP.Lex(Tok);
1979
1980 if (LexID) {
1981 if (Tok.is(tok::identifier)) {
1982 Identifiers.push_back(Tok);
1983 LexID = false;
1984 continue;
1985 }
1986
1987 // Illegal token!
1988 PP.Diag(Tok.getLocation(), diag::warn_pragma_unused_expected_var);
1989 return;
1990 }
1991
1992 // We are execting a ')' or a ','.
1993 if (Tok.is(tok::comma)) {
1994 LexID = true;
1995 continue;
1996 }
1997
1998 if (Tok.is(tok::r_paren)) {
1999 RParenLoc = Tok.getLocation();
2000 break;
2001 }
2002
2003 // Illegal token!
2004 PP.Diag(Tok.getLocation(), diag::warn_pragma_expected_punc) << "unused";
2005 return;
2006 }
2007
2008 PP.Lex(Tok);
2009 if (Tok.isNot(tok::eod)) {
2010 PP.Diag(Tok.getLocation(), diag::warn_pragma_extra_tokens_at_eol) <<
2011 "unused";
2012 return;
2013 }
2014
2015 // Verify that we have a location for the right parenthesis.
2016 assert(RParenLoc.isValid() && "Valid '#pragma unused' must have ')'");
2017 assert(!Identifiers.empty() && "Valid '#pragma unused' must have arguments");
2018
2019 // For each identifier token, insert into the token stream a
2020 // annot_pragma_unused token followed by the identifier token.
2021 // This allows us to cache a "#pragma unused" that occurs inside an inline
2022 // C++ member function.
2023
2024 MutableArrayRef<Token> Toks(
2025 PP.getPreprocessorAllocator().Allocate<Token>(2 * Identifiers.size()),
2026 2 * Identifiers.size());
2027 for (unsigned i=0; i != Identifiers.size(); i++) {
2028 Token &pragmaUnusedTok = Toks[2*i], &idTok = Toks[2*i+1];
2029 pragmaUnusedTok.startToken();
2030 pragmaUnusedTok.setKind(tok::annot_pragma_unused);
2031 pragmaUnusedTok.setLocation(UnusedLoc);
2032 idTok = Identifiers[i];
2033 }
2034 PP.EnterTokenStream(Toks, /*DisableMacroExpansion=*/true,
2035 /*IsReinject=*/false);
2036}

2038// #pragma weak identifier
2039// #pragma weak identifier '=' identifier
2040void PragmaWeakHandler::HandlePragma(Preprocessor &PP,
2041 PragmaIntroducer Introducer,
2042 Token &WeakTok) {
2043 SourceLocation WeakLoc = WeakTok.getLocation();
2044
2045 Token Tok;
2046 PP.Lex(Tok);
2047 if (Tok.isNot(tok::identifier)) {
2048 PP.Diag(Tok.getLocation(), diag::warn_pragma_expected_identifier) << "weak";
2049 return;
2050 }
2051
2052 Token WeakName = Tok;
2053 bool HasAlias = false;
2054 Token AliasName;
2055
2056 PP.Lex(Tok);
2057 if (Tok.is(tok::equal)) {
2058 HasAlias = true;
2059 PP.Lex(Tok);
2060 if (Tok.isNot(tok::identifier)) {
2061 PP.Diag(Tok.getLocation(), diag::warn_pragma_expected_identifier)
2062 << "weak";
2063 return;
2064 }
2065 AliasName = Tok;
2066 PP.Lex(Tok);
2067 }
2068
2069 if (Tok.isNot(tok::eod)) {
2070 PP.Diag(Tok.getLocation(), diag::warn_pragma_extra_tokens_at_eol) << "weak";
2071 return;
2072 }
2073
2074 if (HasAlias) {
2075 MutableArrayRef<Token> Toks(
2076 PP.getPreprocessorAllocator().Allocate<Token>(3), 3);
2077 Token &pragmaUnusedTok = Toks[0];
2078 pragmaUnusedTok.startToken();
2079 pragmaUnusedTok.setKind(tok::annot_pragma_weakalias);
2080 pragmaUnusedTok.setLocation(WeakLoc);
2081 pragmaUnusedTok.setAnnotationEndLoc(AliasName.getLocation());
2082 Toks[1] = WeakName;
2083 Toks[2] = AliasName;
2084 PP.EnterTokenStream(Toks, /*DisableMacroExpansion=*/true,
2085 /*IsReinject=*/false);
2086 } else {
2087 MutableArrayRef<Token> Toks(
2088 PP.getPreprocessorAllocator().Allocate<Token>(2), 2);
2089 Token &pragmaUnusedTok = Toks[0];
2090 pragmaUnusedTok.startToken();
2091 pragmaUnusedTok.setKind(tok::annot_pragma_weak);
2092 pragmaUnusedTok.setLocation(WeakLoc);
2093 pragmaUnusedTok.setAnnotationEndLoc(WeakLoc);
2094 Toks[1] = WeakName;
2095 PP.EnterTokenStream(Toks, /*DisableMacroExpansion=*/true,
2096 /*IsReinject=*/false);
2097 }
2098}

2204void PragmaOpenCLExtensionHandler::HandlePragma(Preprocessor &PP,
2205 PragmaIntroducer Introducer,
2206 Token &Tok) {
2207 PP.LexUnexpandedToken(Tok);
2208 if (Tok.isNot(tok::identifier)) {
2209 PP.Diag(Tok.getLocation(), diag::warn_pragma_expected_identifier) <<
2210 "OPENCL";
2211 return;
2212 }
2213 IdentifierInfo *Ext = Tok.getIdentifierInfo();
2214 SourceLocation NameLoc = Tok.getLocation();
2215
2216 PP.Lex(Tok);
2217 if (Tok.isNot(tok::colon)) {
2218 PP.Diag(Tok.getLocation(), diag::warn_pragma_expected_colon) << Ext;
2219 return;
2220 }
2221
2222 PP.Lex(Tok);
2223 if (Tok.isNot(tok::identifier)) {
2224 PP.Diag(Tok.getLocation(), diag::warn_pragma_expected_predicate) << 0;
2225 return;
2226 }
2227 IdentifierInfo *Pred = Tok.getIdentifierInfo();
2228
2229 OpenCLExtState State;
2230 if (Pred->isStr("enable")) {
2231 State = Enable;
2232 } else if (Pred->isStr("disable")) {
2233 State = Disable;
2234 } else if (Pred->isStr("begin"))
2235 State = Begin;
2236 else if (Pred->isStr("end"))
2237 State = End;
2238 else {
2239 PP.Diag(Tok.getLocation(), diag::warn_pragma_expected_predicate)
2240 << Ext->isStr("all");
2241 return;
2242 }
2243 SourceLocation StateLoc = Tok.getLocation();
2244
2245 PP.Lex(Tok);
2246 if (Tok.isNot(tok::eod)) {
2247 PP.Diag(Tok.getLocation(), diag::warn_pragma_extra_tokens_at_eol) <<
2248 "OPENCL EXTENSION";
2249 return;
2250 }
2251
2252 auto Info = PP.getPreprocessorAllocator().Allocate<OpenCLExtData>(1);
2253 Info->first = Ext;
2254 Info->second = State;
2255 MutableArrayRef<Token> Toks(PP.getPreprocessorAllocator().Allocate<Token>(1),
2256 1);
2257 Toks[0].startToken();
2258 Toks[0].setKind(tok::annot_pragma_opencl_extension);
2259 Toks[0].setLocation(NameLoc);
2260 Toks[0].setAnnotationValue(static_cast<void*>(Info));
2261 Toks[0].setAnnotationEndLoc(StateLoc);
2262 PP.EnterTokenStream(Toks, /*DisableMacroExpansion=*/true,
2263 /*IsReinject=*/false);
2264
2265 if (PP.getPPCallbacks())
2266 PP.getPPCallbacks()->PragmaOpenCLExtension(NameLoc, Ext,
2267 StateLoc, State);
2268}

2284/// Handle '#pragma omp ...' when OpenMP is enabled.
2285///
2286void PragmaOpenMPHandler::HandlePragma(Preprocessor &PP,
2287 PragmaIntroducer Introducer,
2288 Token &FirstTok) {
2289 SmallVector<Token, 16> Pragma;
2290 Token Tok;
2291 Tok.startToken();
2292 Tok.setKind(tok::annot_pragma_openmp);
2293 Tok.setLocation(Introducer.Loc);
2294
2295 while (Tok.isNot(tok::eod) && Tok.isNot(tok::eof)) {
2296 Pragma.push_back(Tok);
2297 PP.Lex(Tok);
2298 if (Tok.is(tok::annot_pragma_openmp)) {
2299 PP.Diag(Tok, diag::err_omp_unexpected_directive) << 0;
2300 unsigned InnerPragmaCnt = 1;
2301 while (InnerPragmaCnt != 0) {
2302 PP.Lex(Tok);
2303 if (Tok.is(tok::annot_pragma_openmp))
2304 ++InnerPragmaCnt;
2305 else if (Tok.is(tok::annot_pragma_openmp_end))
2306 --InnerPragmaCnt;
2307 }
2308 PP.Lex(Tok);
2309 }
2310 }
2311 SourceLocation EodLoc = Tok.getLocation();
2312 Tok.startToken();
2313 Tok.setKind(tok::annot_pragma_openmp_end);
2314 Tok.setLocation(EodLoc);
2315 Pragma.push_back(Tok);
2316
2317 auto Toks = llvm::make_unique<Token[]>(Pragma.size());
2318 std::copy(Pragma.begin(), Pragma.end(), Toks.get());
2319 PP.EnterTokenStream(std::move(Toks), Pragma.size(),
2320 /*DisableMacroExpansion=*/false, /*IsReinject=*/false);
2321}

2323/// Handle '#pragma pointers_to_members'
2324// The grammar for this pragma is as follows:
2325//
2326// <inheritance model> ::= ('single' | 'multiple' | 'virtual') '_inheritance'
2327//
2328// #pragma pointers_to_members '(' 'best_case' ')'
2329// #pragma pointers_to_members '(' 'full_generality' [',' inheritance-model] ')'
2330// #pragma pointers_to_members '(' inheritance-model ')'
2331void PragmaMSPointersToMembers::HandlePragma(Preprocessor &PP,
2332 PragmaIntroducer Introducer,
2333 Token &Tok) {
2334 SourceLocation PointersToMembersLoc = Tok.getLocation();
2335 PP.Lex(Tok);
2336 if (Tok.isNot(tok::l_paren)) {
2337 PP.Diag(PointersToMembersLoc, diag::warn_pragma_expected_lparen)
2338 << "pointers_to_members";
2339 return;
2340 }
2341 PP.Lex(Tok);
2342 const IdentifierInfo *Arg = Tok.getIdentifierInfo();
2343 if (!Arg) {
2344 PP.Diag(Tok.getLocation(), diag::warn_pragma_expected_identifier)
2345 << "pointers_to_members";
2346 return;
2347 }
2348 PP.Lex(Tok);
2349
2350 LangOptions::PragmaMSPointersToMembersKind RepresentationMethod;
2351 if (Arg->isStr("best_case")) {
2352 RepresentationMethod = LangOptions::PPTMK_BestCase;
2353 } else {
2354 if (Arg->isStr("full_generality")) {
2355 if (Tok.is(tok::comma)) {
2356 PP.Lex(Tok);
2357
2358 Arg = Tok.getIdentifierInfo();
2359 if (!Arg) {
2360 PP.Diag(Tok.getLocation(),
2361 diag::err_pragma_pointers_to_members_unknown_kind)
2362 << Tok.getKind() << /*OnlyInheritanceModels*/ 0;
2363 return;
2364 }
2365 PP.Lex(Tok);
2366 } else if (Tok.is(tok::r_paren)) {
2367 // #pragma pointers_to_members(full_generality) implicitly specifies
2368 // virtual_inheritance.
2369 Arg = nullptr;
2370 RepresentationMethod = LangOptions::PPTMK_FullGeneralityVirtualInheritance;
2371 } else {
2372 PP.Diag(Tok.getLocation(), diag::err_expected_punc)
2373 << "full_generality";
2374 return;
2375 }
2376 }
2377
2378 if (Arg) {
2379 if (Arg->isStr("single_inheritance")) {
2380 RepresentationMethod =
2381 LangOptions::PPTMK_FullGeneralitySingleInheritance;
2382 } else if (Arg->isStr("multiple_inheritance")) {
2383 RepresentationMethod =
2384 LangOptions::PPTMK_FullGeneralityMultipleInheritance;
2385 } else if (Arg->isStr("virtual_inheritance")) {
2386 RepresentationMethod =
2387 LangOptions::PPTMK_FullGeneralityVirtualInheritance;
2388 } else {
2389 PP.Diag(Tok.getLocation(),
2390 diag::err_pragma_pointers_to_members_unknown_kind)
2391 << Arg << /*HasPointerDeclaration*/ 1;
2392 return;
2393 }
2394 }
2395 }
2396
2397 if (Tok.isNot(tok::r_paren)) {
2398 PP.Diag(Tok.getLocation(), diag::err_expected_rparen_after)
2399 << (Arg ? Arg->getName() : "full_generality");
2400 return;
2401 }
2402
2403 SourceLocation EndLoc = Tok.getLocation();
2404 PP.Lex(Tok);
2405 if (Tok.isNot(tok::eod)) {
2406 PP.Diag(Tok.getLocation(), diag::warn_pragma_extra_tokens_at_eol)
2407 << "pointers_to_members";
2408 return;
2409 }
2410
2411 Token AnnotTok;
2412 AnnotTok.startToken();
2413 AnnotTok.setKind(tok::annot_pragma_ms_pointers_to_members);
2414 AnnotTok.setLocation(PointersToMembersLoc);
2415 AnnotTok.setAnnotationEndLoc(EndLoc);
2416 AnnotTok.setAnnotationValue(
2417 reinterpret_cast<void *>(static_cast<uintptr_t>(RepresentationMethod)));
2418 PP.EnterToken(AnnotTok, /*IsReinject=*/true);
2419}

2421/// Handle '#pragma vtordisp'
2422// The grammar for this pragma is as follows:
2423//
2424// <vtordisp-mode> ::= ('off' | 'on' | '0' | '1' | '2' )
2425//
2426// #pragma vtordisp '(' ['push' ','] vtordisp-mode ')'
2427// #pragma vtordisp '(' 'pop' ')'
2428// #pragma vtordisp '(' ')'
2429void PragmaMSVtorDisp::HandlePragma(Preprocessor &PP,
2430 PragmaIntroducer Introducer, Token &Tok) {
2431 SourceLocation VtorDispLoc = Tok.getLocation();
2432 PP.Lex(Tok);
2433 if (Tok.isNot(tok::l_paren)) {
2434 PP.Diag(VtorDispLoc, diag::warn_pragma_expected_lparen) << "vtordisp";
2435 return;
2436 }
2437 PP.Lex(Tok);
2438
2439 Sema::PragmaMsStackAction Action = Sema::PSK_Set;
2440 const IdentifierInfo *II = Tok.getIdentifierInfo();
2441 if (II) {
2442 if (II->isStr("push")) {
2443 // #pragma vtordisp(push, mode)
2444 PP.Lex(Tok);
2445 if (Tok.isNot(tok::comma)) {
2446 PP.Diag(VtorDispLoc, diag::warn_pragma_expected_punc) << "vtordisp";
2447 return;
2448 }
2449 PP.Lex(Tok);
2450 Action = Sema::PSK_Push_Set;
2451 // not push, could be on/off
2452 } else if (II->isStr("pop")) {
2453 // #pragma vtordisp(pop)
2454 PP.Lex(Tok);
2455 Action = Sema::PSK_Pop;
2456 }
2457 // not push or pop, could be on/off
2458 } else {
2459 if (Tok.is(tok::r_paren)) {
2460 // #pragma vtordisp()
2461 Action = Sema::PSK_Reset;
2462 }
2463 }
2464
2465
2466 uint64_t Value = 0;
2467 if (Action & Sema::PSK_Push || Action & Sema::PSK_Set) {
2468 const IdentifierInfo *II = Tok.getIdentifierInfo();
2469 if (II && II->isStr("off")) {
2470 PP.Lex(Tok);
2471 Value = 0;
2472 } else if (II && II->isStr("on")) {
2473 PP.Lex(Tok);
2474 Value = 1;
2475 } else if (Tok.is(tok::numeric_constant) &&
2476 PP.parseSimpleIntegerLiteral(Tok, Value)) {
2477 if (Value > 2) {
2478 PP.Diag(Tok.getLocation(), diag::warn_pragma_expected_integer)
2479 << 0 << 2 << "vtordisp";
2480 return;
2481 }
2482 } else {
2483 PP.Diag(Tok.getLocation(), diag::warn_pragma_invalid_action)
2484 << "vtordisp";
2485 return;
2486 }
2487 }
2488
2489 // Finish the pragma: ')' $
2490 if (Tok.isNot(tok::r_paren)) {
2491 PP.Diag(VtorDispLoc, diag::warn_pragma_expected_rparen) << "vtordisp";
2492 return;
2493 }
2494 SourceLocation EndLoc = Tok.getLocation();
2495 PP.Lex(Tok);
2496 if (Tok.isNot(tok::eod)) {
2497 PP.Diag(Tok.getLocation(), diag::warn_pragma_extra_tokens_at_eol)
2498 << "vtordisp";
2499 return;
2500 }
2501
2502 // Enter the annotation.
2503 Token AnnotTok;
2504 AnnotTok.startToken();
2505 AnnotTok.setKind(tok::annot_pragma_ms_vtordisp);
2506 AnnotTok.setLocation(VtorDispLoc);
2507 AnnotTok.setAnnotationEndLoc(EndLoc);
2508 AnnotTok.setAnnotationValue(reinterpret_cast<void *>(
2509 static_cast<uintptr_t>((Action << 16) | (Value & 0xFFFF))));
2510 PP.EnterToken(AnnotTok, /*IsReinject=*/false);
2511}
2512
2513/// Handle all MS pragmas. Simply forwards the tokens after inserting
2514/// an annotation token.
2515void PragmaMSPragma::HandlePragma(Preprocessor &PP,
2516 PragmaIntroducer Introducer, Token &Tok) {
2517 Token EoF, AnnotTok;
2518 EoF.startToken();
2519 EoF.setKind(tok::eof);
2520 AnnotTok.startToken();
2521 AnnotTok.setKind(tok::annot_pragma_ms_pragma);
2522 AnnotTok.setLocation(Tok.getLocation());
2523 AnnotTok.setAnnotationEndLoc(Tok.getLocation());
2524 SmallVector<Token, 8> TokenVector;
2525 // Suck up all of the tokens before the eod.
2526 for (; Tok.isNot(tok::eod); PP.Lex(Tok)) {
2527 TokenVector.push_back(Tok);
2528 AnnotTok.setAnnotationEndLoc(Tok.getLocation());
2529 }
2530 // Add a sentinel EoF token to the end of the list.
2531 TokenVector.push_back(EoF);
2532 // We must allocate this array with new because EnterTokenStream is going to
2533 // delete it later.
2534 auto TokenArray = llvm::make_unique<Token[]>(TokenVector.size());
2535 std::copy(TokenVector.begin(), TokenVector.end(), TokenArray.get());
2536 auto Value = new (PP.getPreprocessorAllocator())
2537 std::pair<std::unique_ptr<Token[]>, size_t>(std::move(TokenArray),
2538 TokenVector.size());
2539 AnnotTok.setAnnotationValue(Value);
2540 PP.EnterToken(AnnotTok, /*IsReinject*/ false);
2541}

2543/// Handle the Microsoft \#pragma detect_mismatch extension.
2544///
2545/// The syntax is:
2546/// \code
2547/// #pragma detect_mismatch("name", "value")
2548/// \endcode
2549/// Where 'name' and 'value' are quoted strings. The values are embedded in
2550/// the object file and passed along to the linker. If the linker detects a
2551/// mismatch in the object file's values for the given name, a LNK2038 error
2552/// is emitted. See MSDN for more details.
2553void PragmaDetectMismatchHandler::HandlePragma(Preprocessor &PP,
2554 PragmaIntroducer Introducer,
2555 Token &Tok) {
2556 SourceLocation DetectMismatchLoc = Tok.getLocation();
2557 PP.Lex(Tok);
2558 if (Tok.isNot(tok::l_paren)) {
2559 PP.Diag(DetectMismatchLoc, diag::err_expected) << tok::l_paren;
2560 return;
2561 }
2562
2563 // Read the name to embed, which must be a string literal.
2564 std::string NameString;
2565 if (!PP.LexStringLiteral(Tok, NameString,
2566 "pragma detect_mismatch",
2567 /*MacroExpansion=*/true))
2568 return;
2569
2570 // Read the comma followed by a second string literal.
2571 std::string ValueString;
2572 if (Tok.isNot(tok::comma)) {
2573 PP.Diag(Tok.getLocation(), diag::err_pragma_detect_mismatch_malformed);
2574 return;
2575 }
2576
2577 if (!PP.LexStringLiteral(Tok, ValueString, "pragma detect_mismatch",
2578 /*MacroExpansion=*/true))
2579 return;
2580
2581 if (Tok.isNot(tok::r_paren)) {
2582 PP.Diag(Tok.getLocation(), diag::err_expected) << tok::r_paren;
2583 return;
2584 }
2585 PP.Lex(Tok); // Eat the r_paren.
2586
2587 if (Tok.isNot(tok::eod)) {
2588 PP.Diag(Tok.getLocation(), diag::err_pragma_detect_mismatch_malformed);
2589 return;
2590 }
2591
2592 // If the pragma is lexically sound, notify any interested PPCallbacks.
2593 if (PP.getPPCallbacks())
2594 PP.getPPCallbacks()->PragmaDetectMismatch(DetectMismatchLoc, NameString,
2595 ValueString);
2596
2597 Actions.ActOnPragmaDetectMismatch(DetectMismatchLoc, NameString, ValueString);
2598}

2600/// Handle the microsoft \#pragma comment extension.
2601///
2602/// The syntax is:
2603/// \code
2604/// #pragma comment(linker, "foo")
2605/// \endcode
2606/// 'linker' is one of five identifiers: compiler, exestr, lib, linker, user.
2607/// "foo" is a string, which is fully macro expanded, and permits string
2608/// concatenation, embedded escape characters etc. See MSDN for more details.
2609void PragmaCommentHandler::HandlePragma(Preprocessor &PP,
2610 PragmaIntroducer Introducer,
2611 Token &Tok) {
2612 SourceLocation CommentLoc = Tok.getLocation();
2613 PP.Lex(Tok);
2614 if (Tok.isNot(tok::l_paren)) {
2615 PP.Diag(CommentLoc, diag::err_pragma_comment_malformed);
2616 return;
2617 }
2618
2619 // Read the identifier.
2620 PP.Lex(Tok);
2621 if (Tok.isNot(tok::identifier)) {
2622 PP.Diag(CommentLoc, diag::err_pragma_comment_malformed);
2623 return;
2624 }
2625
2626 // Verify that this is one of the 5 whitelisted options.
2627 IdentifierInfo *II = Tok.getIdentifierInfo();
2628 PragmaMSCommentKind Kind =
2629 llvm::StringSwitch<PragmaMSCommentKind>(II->getName())
2630 .Case("linker", PCK_Linker)
2631 .Case("lib", PCK_Lib)
2632 .Case("compiler", PCK_Compiler)
2633 .Case("exestr", PCK_ExeStr)
2634 .Case("user", PCK_User)
2635 .Default(PCK_Unknown);
2636 if (Kind == PCK_Unknown) {
2637 PP.Diag(Tok.getLocation(), diag::err_pragma_comment_unknown_kind);
2638 return;
2639 }
2640
2641 if (PP.getTargetInfo().getTriple().isOSBinFormatELF() && Kind != PCK_Lib) {
2642 PP.Diag(Tok.getLocation(), diag::warn_pragma_comment_ignored)
2643 << II->getName();
2644 return;
2645 }
2646
2647 // On PS4, issue a warning about any pragma comments other than
2648 // #pragma comment lib.
2649 if (PP.getTargetInfo().getTriple().isPS4() && Kind != PCK_Lib) {
2650 PP.Diag(Tok.getLocation(), diag::warn_pragma_comment_ignored)
2651 << II->getName();
2652 return;
2653 }
2654
2655 // Read the optional string if present.
2656 PP.Lex(Tok);
2657 std::string ArgumentString;
2658 if (Tok.is(tok::comma) && !PP.LexStringLiteral(Tok, ArgumentString,
2659 "pragma comment",
2660 /*MacroExpansion=*/true))
2661 return;
2662
2663 // FIXME: warn that 'exestr' is deprecated.
2664 // FIXME: If the kind is "compiler" warn if the string is present (it is
2665 // ignored).
2666 // The MSDN docs say that "lib" and "linker" require a string and have a short
2667 // whitelist of linker options they support, but in practice MSVC doesn't
2668 // issue a diagnostic. Therefore neither does clang.
2669
2670 if (Tok.isNot(tok::r_paren)) {
2671 PP.Diag(Tok.getLocation(), diag::err_pragma_comment_malformed);
2672 return;
2673 }
2674 PP.Lex(Tok); // eat the r_paren.
2675
2676 if (Tok.isNot(tok::eod)) {
2677 PP.Diag(Tok.getLocation(), diag::err_pragma_comment_malformed);
2678 return;
2679 }
2680
2681 // If the pragma is lexically sound, notify any interested PPCallbacks.
2682 if (PP.getPPCallbacks())
2683 PP.getPPCallbacks()->PragmaComment(CommentLoc, II, ArgumentString);
2684
2685 Actions.ActOnPragmaMSComment(CommentLoc, Kind, ArgumentString);
2686}

2688// #pragma clang optimize off
2689// #pragma clang optimize on
2690void PragmaOptimizeHandler::HandlePragma(Preprocessor &PP,
2691 PragmaIntroducer Introducer,
2692 Token &FirstToken) {
2693 Token Tok;
2694 PP.Lex(Tok);
2695 if (Tok.is(tok::eod)) {
2696 PP.Diag(Tok.getLocation(), diag::err_pragma_missing_argument)
2697 << "clang optimize" << /*Expected=*/true << "'on' or 'off'";
2698 return;
2699 }
2700 if (Tok.isNot(tok::identifier)) {
2701 PP.Diag(Tok.getLocation(), diag::err_pragma_optimize_invalid_argument)
2702 << PP.getSpelling(Tok);
2703 return;
2704 }
2705 const IdentifierInfo *II = Tok.getIdentifierInfo();
2706 // The only accepted values are 'on' or 'off'.
2707 bool IsOn = false;
2708 if (II->isStr("on")) {
2709 IsOn = true;
2710 } else if (!II->isStr("off")) {

2712 << PP.getSpelling(Tok);
2713 return;
2714 }
2715 PP.Lex(Tok);
2716
2717 if (Tok.isNot(tok::eod)) {
2718 PP.Diag(Tok.getLocation(), diag::err_pragma_optimize_extra_argument)
2719 << PP.getSpelling(Tok);
2720 return;
2721 }
2722
2723 Actions.ActOnPragmaOptimize(IsOn, FirstToken.getLocation());
