2727/// Used as the annotation value for tok::annot_pragma_fp.
2728struct TokFPAnnotValue {
2729 enum FlagKinds { Contract };
2730 enum FlagValues { On, Off, Fast };
2731
2732 FlagKinds FlagKind;
2733 FlagValues FlagValue;
2734};

2737void PragmaFPHandler::HandlePragma(Preprocessor &PP,
2738 PragmaIntroducer Introducer, Token &Tok) {
2739 // fp
2740 Token PragmaName = Tok;
2741 SmallVector<Token, 1> TokenList;
2742
2743 PP.Lex(Tok);
2744 if (Tok.isNot(tok::identifier)) {
2745 PP.Diag(Tok.getLocation(), diag::err_pragma_fp_invalid_option)
2746 << /*MissingOption=*/true << "";
2747 return;
2748 }
2749
2750 while (Tok.is(tok::identifier)) {
2751 IdentifierInfo *OptionInfo = Tok.getIdentifierInfo();
2752
2753 auto FlagKind =
2754 llvm::StringSwitch<llvm::Optional<TokFPAnnotValue::FlagKinds>>(
2755 OptionInfo->getName())
2756 .Case("contract", TokFPAnnotValue::Contract)
2757 .Default(None);
2758 if (!FlagKind) {
2759 PP.Diag(Tok.getLocation(), diag::err_pragma_fp_invalid_option)
2760 << /*MissingOption=*/false << OptionInfo;
2761 return;
2762 }
2763 PP.Lex(Tok);
2764
2765 // Read '('
2766 if (Tok.isNot(tok::l_paren)) {
2767 PP.Diag(Tok.getLocation(), diag::err_expected) << tok::l_paren;
2768 return;
2769 }
2770 PP.Lex(Tok);
2771
2772 if (Tok.isNot(tok::identifier)) {
2773 PP.Diag(Tok.getLocation(), diag::err_pragma_fp_invalid_argument)
2774 << PP.getSpelling(Tok) << OptionInfo->getName();
2775 return;
2776 }
2777 const IdentifierInfo *II = Tok.getIdentifierInfo();
2778
2779 auto FlagValue =
2780 llvm::StringSwitch<llvm::Optional<TokFPAnnotValue::FlagValues>>(
2781 II->getName())
2782 .Case("on", TokFPAnnotValue::On)
2783 .Case("off", TokFPAnnotValue::Off)
2784 .Case("fast", TokFPAnnotValue::Fast)
2785 .Default(llvm::None);
2786
2787 if (!FlagValue) {
2788 PP.Diag(Tok.getLocation(), diag::err_pragma_fp_invalid_argument)
2789 << PP.getSpelling(Tok) << OptionInfo->getName();
2790 return;
2791 }
2792 PP.Lex(Tok);
2793
2794 // Read ')'
2795 if (Tok.isNot(tok::r_paren)) {
2796 PP.Diag(Tok.getLocation(), diag::err_expected) << tok::r_paren;
2797 return;
2798 }
2799 PP.Lex(Tok);
2800
2801 auto *AnnotValue = new (PP.getPreprocessorAllocator())
2802 TokFPAnnotValue{*FlagKind, *FlagValue};
2803 // Generate the loop hint token.
2804 Token FPTok;
2805 FPTok.startToken();
2806 FPTok.setKind(tok::annot_pragma_fp);
2807 FPTok.setLocation(PragmaName.getLocation());
2808 FPTok.setAnnotationEndLoc(PragmaName.getLocation());
2809 FPTok.setAnnotationValue(reinterpret_cast<void *>(AnnotValue));
2810 TokenList.push_back(FPTok);
2811 }
2812
2813 if (Tok.isNot(tok::eod)) {
2814 PP.Diag(Tok.getLocation(), diag::warn_pragma_extra_tokens_at_eol)
2815 << "clang fp";
2816 return;
2817 }
2818
2819 auto TokenArray = llvm::make_unique<Token[]>(TokenList.size());
2820 std::copy(TokenList.begin(), TokenList.end(), TokenArray.get());
2821
2822 PP.EnterTokenStream(std::move(TokenArray), TokenList.size(),
2823 /*DisableMacroExpansion=*/false, /*IsReinject=*/false);
2824}

2826void Parser::HandlePragmaFP() {

2848/// Parses loop or unroll pragma hint value and fills in Info.
2849static bool ParseLoopHintValue(Preprocessor &PP, Token &Tok, Token PragmaName,
2850 Token Option, bool ValueInParens,
2851 PragmaLoopHintInfo &Info) {
2852 SmallVector<Token, 1> ValueList;
2853 int OpenParens = ValueInParens ? 1 : 0;
2854 // Read constant expression.
2855 while (Tok.isNot(tok::eod)) {
2856 if (Tok.is(tok::l_paren))
2857 OpenParens++;
2858 else if (Tok.is(tok::r_paren)) {
2859 OpenParens--;
2860 if (OpenParens == 0 && ValueInParens)
2861 break;
2862 }
2863
2864 ValueList.push_back(Tok);
2865 PP.Lex(Tok);
2866 }
2867
2868 if (ValueInParens) {
2869 // Read ')'
2870 if (Tok.isNot(tok::r_paren)) {
2871 PP.Diag(Tok.getLocation(), diag::err_expected) << tok::r_paren;
2872 return true;
2873 }
2874 PP.Lex(Tok);
2875 }
2876
2877 Token EOFTok;
2878 EOFTok.startToken();
2879 EOFTok.setKind(tok::eof);
2880 EOFTok.setLocation(Tok.getLocation());
2881 ValueList.push_back(EOFTok); // Terminates expression for parsing.
2882
2883 Info.Toks = llvm::makeArrayRef(ValueList).copy(PP.getPreprocessorAllocator());
2884
2885 Info.PragmaName = PragmaName;
2886 Info.Option = Option;
2887 return false;
2888}

2890/// Handle the \#pragma clang loop directive.
2891/// #pragma clang 'loop' loop-hints
2892///
2893/// loop-hints:
2894/// loop-hint loop-hints[opt]
2895///
2896/// loop-hint:
2897/// 'vectorize' '(' loop-hint-keyword ')'
2898/// 'interleave' '(' loop-hint-keyword ')'
2899/// 'unroll' '(' unroll-hint-keyword ')'
2900/// 'vectorize_width' '(' loop-hint-value ')'
2901/// 'interleave_count' '(' loop-hint-value ')'
2902/// 'unroll_count' '(' loop-hint-value ')'
2903/// 'pipeline' '(' disable ')'
2904/// 'pipeline_initiation_interval' '(' loop-hint-value ')'
2905///
2906/// loop-hint-keyword:
2907/// 'enable'
2908/// 'disable'
2909/// 'assume_safety'
2910///
2911/// unroll-hint-keyword:
2912/// 'enable'
2913/// 'disable'
2914/// 'full'
2915///
2916/// loop-hint-value:
2917/// constant-expression
2918///
2919/// Specifying vectorize(enable) or vectorize_width(_value_) instructs llvm to
2920/// try vectorizing the instructions of the loop it precedes. Specifying
2921/// interleave(enable) or interleave_count(_value_) instructs llvm to try
2922/// interleaving multiple iterations of the loop it precedes. The width of the
2923/// vector instructions is specified by vectorize_width() and the number of
2924/// interleaved loop iterations is specified by interleave_count(). Specifying a
2925/// value of 1 effectively disables vectorization/interleaving, even if it is
2926/// possible and profitable, and 0 is invalid. The loop vectorizer currently
2927/// only works on inner loops.
2928///
2929/// The unroll and unroll_count directives control the concatenation
2930/// unroller. Specifying unroll(enable) instructs llvm to unroll the loop
2931/// completely if the trip count is known at compile time and unroll partially
2932/// if the trip count is not known. Specifying unroll(full) is similar to
2933/// unroll(enable) but will unroll the loop only if the trip count is known at
2934/// compile time. Specifying unroll(disable) disables unrolling for the
2935/// loop. Specifying unroll_count(_value_) instructs llvm to try to unroll the
2936/// loop the number of times indicated by the value.
2937void PragmaLoopHintHandler::HandlePragma(Preprocessor &PP,
2938 PragmaIntroducer Introducer,
2939 Token &Tok) {
2940 // Incoming token is "loop" from "#pragma clang loop".
2941 Token PragmaName = Tok;
2942 SmallVector<Token, 1> TokenList;
2943
2944 // Lex the optimization option and verify it is an identifier.
2945 PP.Lex(Tok);
2946 if (Tok.isNot(tok::identifier)) {
2947 PP.Diag(Tok.getLocation(), diag::err_pragma_loop_invalid_option)
2948 << /*MissingOption=*/true << "";
2949 return;
2950 }
2951
2952 while (Tok.is(tok::identifier)) {
2953 Token Option = Tok;
2954 IdentifierInfo *OptionInfo = Tok.getIdentifierInfo();
2955
2956 bool OptionValid = llvm::StringSwitch<bool>(OptionInfo->getName())
2957 .Case("vectorize", true)
2958 .Case("interleave", true)
2959 .Case("unroll", true)
2960 .Case("distribute", true)
2961 .Case("vectorize_width", true)
2962 .Case("interleave_count", true)
2963 .Case("unroll_count", true)
2964 .Case("pipeline", true)
2965 .Case("pipeline_initiation_interval", true)
2966 .Default(false);
2967 if (!OptionValid) {
2968 PP.Diag(Tok.getLocation(), diag::err_pragma_loop_invalid_option)
2969 << /*MissingOption=*/false << OptionInfo;
2970 return;
2971 }
2972 PP.Lex(Tok);
2973
2974 // Read '('
2975 if (Tok.isNot(tok::l_paren)) {
2976 PP.Diag(Tok.getLocation(), diag::err_expected) << tok::l_paren;
2977 return;
2978 }
2979 PP.Lex(Tok);
2980
2981 auto *Info = new (PP.getPreprocessorAllocator()) PragmaLoopHintInfo;
2982 if (ParseLoopHintValue(PP, Tok, PragmaName, Option, /*ValueInParens=*/true,
2983 *Info))
2984 return;
2985
2986 // Generate the loop hint token.
2987 Token LoopHintTok;
2988 LoopHintTok.startToken();
2989 LoopHintTok.setKind(tok::annot_pragma_loop_hint);
2990 LoopHintTok.setLocation(PragmaName.getLocation());
2991 LoopHintTok.setAnnotationEndLoc(PragmaName.getLocation());
2992 LoopHintTok.setAnnotationValue(static_cast<void *>(Info));
2993 TokenList.push_back(LoopHintTok);
2994 }
2995
2996 if (Tok.isNot(tok::eod)) {
2997 PP.Diag(Tok.getLocation(), diag::warn_pragma_extra_tokens_at_eol)
2998 << "clang loop";
2999 return;
3000 }
3001
3002 auto TokenArray = llvm::make_unique<Token[]>(TokenList.size());
3003 std::copy(TokenList.begin(), TokenList.end(), TokenArray.get());
3004
3005 PP.EnterTokenStream(std::move(TokenArray), TokenList.size(),
3006 /*DisableMacroExpansion=*/false, /*IsReinject=*/false);
3007}

3009/// Handle the loop unroll optimization pragmas.
3010/// #pragma unroll
3011/// #pragma unroll unroll-hint-value
3012/// #pragma unroll '(' unroll-hint-value ')'
3013/// #pragma nounroll
3014/// #pragma unroll_and_jam
3015/// #pragma unroll_and_jam unroll-hint-value
3016/// #pragma unroll_and_jam '(' unroll-hint-value ')'
3017/// #pragma nounroll_and_jam
3018///
3019/// unroll-hint-value:
3020/// constant-expression
3021///
3022/// Loop unrolling hints can be specified with '#pragma unroll' or
3023/// '#pragma nounroll'. '#pragma unroll' can take a numeric argument optionally
3024/// contained in parentheses. With no argument the directive instructs llvm to
3025/// try to unroll the loop completely. A positive integer argument can be
3026/// specified to indicate the number of times the loop should be unrolled. To
3027/// maximize compatibility with other compilers the unroll count argument can be
3028/// specified with or without parentheses. Specifying, '#pragma nounroll'
3029/// disables unrolling of the loop.
3030void PragmaUnrollHintHandler::HandlePragma(Preprocessor &PP,
3031 PragmaIntroducer Introducer,
3032 Token &Tok) {
3033 // Incoming token is "unroll" for "#pragma unroll", or "nounroll" for
3034 // "#pragma nounroll".
3035 Token PragmaName = Tok;
3036 PP.Lex(Tok);
3037 auto *Info = new (PP.getPreprocessorAllocator()) PragmaLoopHintInfo;
3038 if (Tok.is(tok::eod)) {
3039 // nounroll or unroll pragma without an argument.
3040 Info->PragmaName = PragmaName;
3041 Info->Option.startToken();
3042 } else if (PragmaName.getIdentifierInfo()->getName() == "nounroll" ||
3043 PragmaName.getIdentifierInfo()->getName() == "nounroll_and_jam") {
3044 PP.Diag(Tok.getLocation(), diag::warn_pragma_extra_tokens_at_eol)
3045 << PragmaName.getIdentifierInfo()->getName();
3046 return;
3047 } else {
3048 // Unroll pragma with an argument: "#pragma unroll N" or
3049 // "#pragma unroll(N)".
3050 // Read '(' if it exists.
3051 bool ValueInParens = Tok.is(tok::l_paren);
3052 if (ValueInParens)
3053 PP.Lex(Tok);
3054
3055 Token Option;
3056 Option.startToken();
3057 if (ParseLoopHintValue(PP, Tok, PragmaName, Option, ValueInParens, *Info))
3058 return;
3059
3060 // In CUDA, the argument to '#pragma unroll' should not be contained in
3061 // parentheses.
3062 if (PP.getLangOpts().CUDA && ValueInParens)
3063 PP.Diag(Info->Toks[0].getLocation(),
3064 diag::warn_pragma_unroll_cuda_value_in_parens);
3065
3066 if (Tok.isNot(tok::eod)) {
3067 PP.Diag(Tok.getLocation(), diag::warn_pragma_extra_tokens_at_eol)
3068 << "unroll";
3069 return;
3070 }
3071 }
3072
3073 // Generate the hint token.
3074 auto TokenArray = llvm::make_unique<Token[]>(1);
3075 TokenArray[0].startToken();
3076 TokenArray[0].setKind(tok::annot_pragma_loop_hint);
3077 TokenArray[0].setLocation(PragmaName.getLocation());
3078 TokenArray[0].setAnnotationEndLoc(PragmaName.getLocation());
3079 TokenArray[0].setAnnotationValue(static_cast<void *>(Info));
3080 PP.EnterTokenStream(std::move(TokenArray), 1,
3081 /*DisableMacroExpansion=*/false, /*IsReinject=*/false);
3082}

3139 PP.Lex(Tok);

3141

3169 return;

3171 // We could syntax check the string but it's probably not worth the effort.
3172 PP.Lex(Tok);

3187 PP.Diag(Tok.getLocation(), diag::warn_pragma_invalid_argument)
3188 << PP.getSpelling(Tok) << "optimize" << /*Expected=*/true
3189 << "'on' or 'off'";

3195 PP.Diag(Tok.getLocation(), diag::warn_pragma_expected_rparen) << "optimize";
3196 return;

3198 PP.Lex(Tok);

3200 if (Tok.isNot(tok::eod)) {

3202 << "optimize";
3203 return;
3204 }
3205 PP.Diag(StartLoc, diag::warn_pragma_optimize);
3206}

3208void PragmaForceCUDAHostDeviceHandler::HandlePragma(
3209 Preprocessor &PP, PragmaIntroducer Introducer, Token &Tok) {
3210 Token FirstTok = Tok;
3211
3212 PP.Lex(Tok);
3213 IdentifierInfo *Info = Tok.getIdentifierInfo();
3214 if (!Info || (!Info->isStr("begin") && !Info->isStr("end"))) {
3215 PP.Diag(FirstTok.getLocation(),
3216 diag::warn_pragma_force_cuda_host_device_bad_arg);
3217 return;
3218 }
3219
3220 if (Info->isStr("begin"))
3221 Actions.PushForceCUDAHostDevice();
3222 else if (!Actions.PopForceCUDAHostDevice())
3223 PP.Diag(FirstTok.getLocation(),
3224 diag::err_pragma_cannot_end_force_cuda_host_device);
3225
3226 PP.Lex(Tok);
3227 if (!Tok.is(tok::eod))
3228 PP.Diag(FirstTok.getLocation(),
3229 diag::warn_pragma_force_cuda_host_device_bad_arg);
3230}

3232/// Handle the #pragma clang attribute directive.
3233///
3234/// The syntax is:
3235/// \code
3236/// #pragma clang attribute push (attribute, subject-set)
3237/// #pragma clang attribute push
3238/// #pragma clang attribute (attribute, subject-set)
3239/// #pragma clang attribute pop
3240/// \endcode
3241///
3242/// There are also 'namespace' variants of push and pop directives. The bare
3243/// '#pragma clang attribute (attribute, subject-set)' version doesn't require a
3244/// namespace, since it always applies attributes to the most recently pushed
3245/// group, regardless of namespace.
3246/// \code
3247/// #pragma clang attribute namespace.push (attribute, subject-set)
3248/// #pragma clang attribute namespace.push
3249/// #pragma clang attribute namespace.pop
3250/// \endcode
3251///
3252/// The subject-set clause defines the set of declarations which receive the
3253/// attribute. Its exact syntax is described in the LanguageExtensions document
3254/// in Clang's documentation.
3255///
3256/// This directive instructs the compiler to begin/finish applying the specified
3257/// attribute to the set of attribute-specific declarations in the active range
3258/// of the pragma.
3259void PragmaAttributeHandler::HandlePragma(Preprocessor &PP,
3260 PragmaIntroducer Introducer,
3261 Token &FirstToken) {
3262 Token Tok;
3263 PP.Lex(Tok);
3264 auto *Info = new (PP.getPreprocessorAllocator())
3265 PragmaAttributeInfo(AttributesForPragmaAttribute);
3266
3267 // Parse the optional namespace followed by a period.
3268 if (Tok.is(tok::identifier)) {
3269 IdentifierInfo *II = Tok.getIdentifierInfo();
3270 if (!II->isStr("push") && !II->isStr("pop")) {
3271 Info->Namespace = II;
3272 PP.Lex(Tok);
3273
3274 if (!Tok.is(tok::period)) {
3275 PP.Diag(Tok.getLocation(), diag::err_pragma_attribute_expected_period)
3276 << II;
3277 return;
3278 }
3279 PP.Lex(Tok);
3280 }
3281 }
3282
3283 if (!Tok.isOneOf(tok::identifier, tok::l_paren)) {
3284 PP.Diag(Tok.getLocation(),
3285 diag::err_pragma_attribute_expected_push_pop_paren);
3286 return;
3287 }
3288
3289 // Determine what action this pragma clang attribute represents.
3290 if (Tok.is(tok::l_paren)) {
3291 if (Info->Namespace) {
3292 PP.Diag(Tok.getLocation(),
3293 diag::err_pragma_attribute_namespace_on_attribute);
3294 PP.Diag(Tok.getLocation(),
3295 diag::note_pragma_attribute_namespace_on_attribute);
3296 return;
3297 }
3298 Info->Action = PragmaAttributeInfo::Attribute;
3299 } else {
3300 const IdentifierInfo *II = Tok.getIdentifierInfo();
3301 if (II->isStr("push"))
3302 Info->Action = PragmaAttributeInfo::Push;
3303 else if (II->isStr("pop"))
3304 Info->Action = PragmaAttributeInfo::Pop;
3305 else {
3306 PP.Diag(Tok.getLocation(), diag::err_pragma_attribute_invalid_argument)
3307 << PP.getSpelling(Tok);
3308 return;
3309 }
3310
3311 PP.Lex(Tok);
3312 }
3313
3314 // Parse the actual attribute.
3315 if ((Info->Action == PragmaAttributeInfo::Push && Tok.isNot(tok::eod)) ||
3316 Info->Action == PragmaAttributeInfo::Attribute) {
3317 if (Tok.isNot(tok::l_paren)) {
3318 PP.Diag(Tok.getLocation(), diag::err_expected) << tok::l_paren;
3319 return;
3320 }
3321 PP.Lex(Tok);
3322
3323 // Lex the attribute tokens.
3324 SmallVector<Token, 16> AttributeTokens;
3325 int OpenParens = 1;
3326 while (Tok.isNot(tok::eod)) {
3327 if (Tok.is(tok::l_paren))
3328 OpenParens++;
3329 else if (Tok.is(tok::r_paren)) {
3330 OpenParens--;
3331 if (OpenParens == 0)
3332 break;
3333 }
3334
3335 AttributeTokens.push_back(Tok);
3336 PP.Lex(Tok);
3337 }
3338
3339 if (AttributeTokens.empty()) {
3340 PP.Diag(Tok.getLocation(), diag::err_pragma_attribute_expected_attribute);
3341 return;
3342 }
3343 if (Tok.isNot(tok::r_paren)) {
3344 PP.Diag(Tok.getLocation(), diag::err_expected) << tok::r_paren;
3345 return;
3346 }
3347 SourceLocation EndLoc = Tok.getLocation();
3348 PP.Lex(Tok);
3349
3350 // Terminate the attribute for parsing.
3351 Token EOFTok;
3352 EOFTok.startToken();
3353 EOFTok.setKind(tok::eof);
3354 EOFTok.setLocation(EndLoc);
3355 AttributeTokens.push_back(EOFTok);
3356
3357 Info->Tokens =
3358 llvm::makeArrayRef(AttributeTokens).copy(PP.getPreprocessorAllocator());
3359 }
3360
3361 if (Tok.isNot(tok::eod))
3362 PP.Diag(Tok.getLocation(), diag::warn_pragma_extra_tokens_at_eol)
3363 << "clang attribute";
3364
3365 // Generate the annotated pragma token.
3366 auto TokenArray = llvm::make_unique<Token[]>(1);
3367 TokenArray[0].startToken();
3368 TokenArray[0].setKind(tok::annot_pragma_attribute);
3369 TokenArray[0].setLocation(FirstToken.getLocation());
3370 TokenArray[0].setAnnotationEndLoc(FirstToken.getLocation());
3371 TokenArray[0].setAnnotationValue(static_cast<void *>(Info));
3372 PP.EnterTokenStream(std::move(TokenArray), 1,
3373 /*DisableMacroExpansion=*/false, /*IsReinject=*/false);
3374}
